Commentary: Fuller length ball outside off, Crawley covers his stumps on this first ball and lets it go to the keeper. Some away movement on this first ball.
Full and outside off again, Crawley once again lets it go to the keeper.
England and Crawley are underway! Full ball around off, Crawley looks to drive but the ball takes the thick inside edge and it goes to square leg for a single.
Good length ball around off, Sibley pushes it back to the bowler.
Shortish ball outside off, it is left alone.

Huge appeal for LBW but not out says the umpire. Length ball coming into the batsman, Sibley looks to defend but misses to get struck on the pads. Philander makes a loud appeal but nothing from the umpire. Philander suggests Faf to go for the review but the skipper tells him that it was probably going over the top.
Hendricks starts with a nasty one! Bangs it on back of a length on middle, Crawley looks to pull but is hit hard on the thigh pad. The ball rolls towards the off side.
Good length ball on middle, driven towards mid on for a single.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Another ball which comes back in from a length. Sibley looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pads.
This one goes away from a length. However, it is way outside off and Sibley shoulders arms.
FOUR! First one of the innings! Hendricks strays on the pads of Sibley on a shortish length, Sibley just helps it down to fine leg and it races away to the fence.
Length ball outside off, it is left alone.
Muted shout from the bowler now. It is a length ball which comes back in sharply. Crawley though is expecting the ball to go away and shoulders arms. He gets hit high on the pads.
Shortish around off, tapped towards point.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
No ball! Another ball which is around off, Crawley comes forward and keeps it out. Philander has overstepped though and it is a no ball.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Good length ball around off, it is blocked off the back foot.
Beauty! A length ball which pitches around off and moves away by a long way. Sibley looks to defend initially but pulls his bat away at the last moment.
Length ball around off, it is defended.
Landed on middle on a length, Sibley is solid in his defense once again.
Good leave! A length ball in the channel outside off, Sibley covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper. Good carry to the keeper there.
Another leave as Hendricks delivers a length ball outside off.
Full ball on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball around off, Crawley defends it off the front foot.
Slips it down the leg this time, Crawley looks to flick but misses.
That wasn't too far away from the off pole. A length ball just outside off, Crawley covers his stumps and lets it be.
FOUR! Driven firmly!  A full ball just outside off, Crawley drills it past the man at mid off. That was timed really nicely by Crawley to bag his first boundary.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Another length ball outside off, Crawley makes another leave.
Bouncer on middle, Sibley ducks under it.
FOUR! Cut away! A shortish length ball outside off, Sibley rocks on the back foot and cuts it through backward point to bag his second boundary of the innings.
Length ball which is shaping away after pitching on middle, Sibley lets it be.
Shortish and on middle, Sibley does well to tuck it towards the leg side.
Length ball around off, it is pushed towards point.
Length ball around off, it is defended off the front foot.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Full ball outside off, Crawley looks to drive but ends up hitting it off the toe end of his willow. It goes straight to the man at covers.
Shortish ball outside off, it is pushed to mid off.
This one is on a length and it is angled into the batter, Crawley tucks it to deep square leg for a couple.
FOUR! Creamed through the covers! A full ball outside off, Crawley gets forward and creams it through the covers and it races away to the fence.
In the channel outside off, Crawley lets it go to the keeper.
Landed on middle on a length, Sibley works it behind square leg for a couple of runs.
Outside off, left alone.

NOT OUT! Hendricks will have to wait for his debut Test wicket. It is a good length ball down the leg side. Sibley looks to flick but misses. The bowler though makes a loud appeal along with the keeper. The umpire takes his time and then raises his fingers. Sibley quickly takes the decision upstairs which means he is quite confident that he did not nick it. The replays roll in and confirm the same. The Ultra Edge detects nothing as the bat crosses the bat. The noise was off the ball hitting the thigh pad. So, the on-field decision has to be changed and Sibley stays. Excellent review from him.
Shortish ball around off, it is punched through covers for a single.
Good length ball around off, Crawley looks to defend but gets an inside edge. The ball goes towards fine leg and a run is taken.
Shortish ball around off, pushed to short fine leg.
FOUR! Welcome to the attack, Anrich Nortje. He bowls a full ball on middle and off, Crawley flicks this one towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Length ball just around off, Crawley looks to defend off the back foot but the ball goes off the thick outside edge towards the man at gully on the bounce.
Full ball swinging in towards the off pole line, pushed towards the man at mid on.
FOUR! Creamed! Outside off delivery yet again, Crawley drives it through the cover region superbly for a boundary.
Full ball on middle and off, Crawley has flicked this one towards the mid-wicket region. The batters manage to run three while the fielders mop it up.
Another one on middle, this time it is flicked in front of square leg and the batters take a single.
Sibley looks to come down the track, Hendricks spots that and bowls it down the leg side. Sibley looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball on the off pole line, it is defended.
Length ball on middle and leg, Sibley gets an inside edge on this one and the ball rolls towards fine leg.
Full ball on off, driven towards the man at mid off.
Down the leg side, Sibley looks to flick but misses.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Good length ball around the off pole line, defended off the front foot.
Length ball on middle and off, defended.
Another one outside off, played towards point.
FOUR! Full length ball on middle and leg, Crawley flicks this ball nicely in the gap at mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length ball down the leg side, Crawley looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad.
Outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to let that one through.
Good length ball on middle and off, defended off the front foot.

No ball! OUT! What! Wait, no! It has been called a No ball! Drama all around and Faf du Plessis just cannot believe it. Length ball outside off, Sibley goes hard at it and cuts. The ball goes to the left at Temba Bavuma at backward point who dives to his left and takes a superb catch but umpire Joel Wilson has called it a no ball as Philander has overstepped. Superb umpiring by Joel Wilson.
Full ball around off, driven towards the man at cover.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
Good length ball on middle and off, driven towards mid off.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Sibley shoulders arms to let that one through.
Full ball on off, pushed towards mid off.
Good length ball on off, left alone by the bowler.
Length ball outside off, left alone by the batsman.
Another one outside off, left alone by Crawley.
The bowlers need to bowl better lines here. Outside off again, Crawley shoulders arms again.
This is poor stuff and Crawley leaves this ball too as it is outside off.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Fullish ball now, but again outside off and left alone. The South African bowlers need to straighten their line here and attack the stumps.
Okay now this seems to be some sort of a strategy as Philander bowls another delivery outside off but Sibley is patient and does not fiddle with it.
Finally one ball which is bowled on the stumps, worked towards square leg for a single.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Good length ball on middle and leg, pushed towards the man at mid on for a quick single.
Another one outside off, Crawley leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley looks to play at it but fails to put bat on ball.
Full ball on off, driven towards the man at mid off.
Another length ball outside off, Crawley lets it go to the keeper.
Full ball on off, driven straight to mid off.
Length ball around off, it is defended.
Another ball in the channel outside off, an easy leave for the batsman.
Shortish ball around off, it is tapped through covers for a couple of runs.
FOUR! 50 up for England. A full ball on middle, Sibley strokes it through mid on and it races away to the fence.
Beaten! Brilliant response from the bowler. Philander bowls it on a length around off and makes it shape away from the forward prod of the batter. It beats the outside edge and goes to the keeper.
Length ball around off, it is pushed to point.
Full ball outside off, Sibley drills the drive but straight to the cover fielder.
Crawley has defended that one off the front foot towards the leg side.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side.
FOUR! Length ball on off, Crawley drives this one off the back foot through the cover region. Pieter Malan gives it a chase but he cannot keep it in despite his dive.
Outside off, left alone.
Beauty! Back of a length ball on off, Crawley looks to defend this one off the back foot but gets completely squared up as the ball moves away.
Full ball on middle and off, driven towards the man at mid on.
Full ball on off, defended.
Another fuller ball around off, it is pushed towards covers.
Full ball on off, defended.
Another full ball around off, this time, Sibley drives it towards mid on.
In the channel outside off, shaping further away. Sibley shoulders arms.
Full ball outside off, pushed to mid off.
Another fuller ball around off, Crawley defends it off the front foot.
Fuller and just outside off, Crawley drives it straight to the man at mid off.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Back of a length ball on middle, it is pulled to deep square leg for a single.
Another length ball outside off, it is defended off the back foot.
A leave to get through the over! It is outside off on a length. It is left alone.
Shortish ball around off, it is defended.
Very full ball on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball around off, it is tapped towards point.
Shortish ball around off, it is defended off the back foot.
Length ball on middle, Crawley looks to defend but the ball goes to short mid-wicket off the inner half of the bat.
On the pads this time, nudged towards fine leg for a single.
Short ball around off, worked towards mid-wicket.
Edged but it does not carry! Good length ball around off, Crawley pokes at it but the ball shapes away and takes the outside edge but falls short of the second slip fielder.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Another ball outside off , left alone.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Another length ball outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Good length ball angled into the batter, it is worked towards mid-wicket where fielder misfields and allows a single.
Full ball around off, it is defended.
Another length ball around off, it is tapped towards point.
Length ball outside off, Sibley covers his stumps and lets it be.
FOUR! Length ball outside off, Sibley guides it through backward point for a boundary.
FOUR! Drilled through the covers! A full ball outside off, Crawley takes a good stride forward and drills it through covers for a boundary.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
FOUR! Whipped off his pads. Poor line this from Pretorius. He bowls it on the pads on a fuller length, Crawley flicks it off his pads and it races away to the fence.
Shortish ball around off and middle, it is blocked off the back foot.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! All timing! Another full ball from Pretorius. Crawley drives it straight down the ground. Pretorius gets down to get a hand to the ball but misses and it goes to the fence.
Slightly short and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone.
Beaten! A length ball that pitches around off and shapes away. Sibley pokes at it without any feet movement and gets beaten.
Slightly shortish ball outside off, pushed to point.
WIDE! Bouncer outside off, it is left alone. Called wide by the umpire.
Another length ball outside off, left alone.
Shortish ball on middle, Sibley hops and blocks it off his back foot.
Leading edge! Full ball on middle, Crawley looks to flick but the ball takes the leading edge and goes to point for a run. Crawley gets to his maiden half ton with that run.
FOUR! Driven handsomely! A full ball on off, Sibley leans into the shot and drills it down the ground. Need not run for that one.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball on middle, Sibley looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half of the bat and goes to square leg for a run.
Very full ball on off, it is defended.
In the channel outside off, Crawley leaves it alone.
Fuller ball around off, it is defended.
Outside off, Sibley lets it go to the keeper.
Slightly short and on the body, it is worked towards mid-wicket for a single.
Slightly shortish ball angled into the batter, Crawley looks to defend but gets an inside edge. The ball hits the pads and rolls towards the off side.
On middle, it is flicked to deep square leg for a run.
Landed on middle on a length, Sibley looks to work it around the leg side but gets hit on the pads.
Full ball on middle, pushed to mid on.
Fullish and just outside off, Crawley covers his stumps and lets it be.

FOUR! Straight as an arrow! This is brilliant batting from Crawley. Hendricks overpitches it outside off, Crawley just times it down the ground firmly. Sibley takes the evasive action at the non-striker's end and falls in the process. The ball goes past him and then races to the fence.
Short of a length ball around off, Crawley pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Bouncer on middle, Sibley ducks under it.
Full ball around off, Sibley watchfully defends it.
Back of a length ball around off, it is blocked off the back foot.
Shortish ball on middle, Crawley once again makes a solid block.
Another shorter length ball on middle, Crawley looks to pull but mistimes it towards mid-wicket.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.

Ouch! Straight on the helmet! Crawley quickly takes off his helmet and walks across to the leg side. It is another short of a length ball which comes into the batter. Crawley swivels and looks to pull but is early in the shot. He misses and the ball hits him on the right side of the helmet. That was a pacy delivery too.
Bouncer and just outside off, it is left alone. Called wide by the umpire as it was way over the batsman. Wided by the umpire.
Outside off, left alone. Finally the over ends.

Landed around off, it is worked towards square leg. A quick single is taken. The fielder there in the attempt of running the batter out concedes an overthrow as he misses his shy at the non-striker's end.
A bouncer on middle, Sibley ducks under it.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side.
Shortish ball around off, Sibley taps it through covers and bags a couple of runs.

Appeal for LBW but this one was probably pitching outside leg. A length ball around middle and leg, Sibley looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Huge appeal from the bowler but the umpire not interested. No review from du Plessis.
Nicely bowled and equally well played! A very full ball on middle, almost a yorker, Sibley does well to flick it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full ball around off, worked towards mid-wicket.
Slightly short and on the body, Crawley blocks it off the back foot.
Full and around off, flicked to mid-wicket by Crawley.
Length ball angled into the batter, Crawley flicks it to deep square leg for a run.

FOUR! 100 up for England. Brilliant opening stand for the visitors. A length ball on middle, Sibley goes on the back foot and flicks it past the short leg fielder. There was shout of 'catch it' but it was flicked with power and there was no chance the fielder would've been even getting his hands to it. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1.
A lose short on the first ball post the break! A good length ball outside off, Crawley goes chasing after it and looks to drive but misses. Luckily, does not get an edge on that one.
Shortish ball on middle, Crawley blocks it off the back foot.
Another short of a length ball on middle, it is pulled to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball on the pads, Crawley looks to flick but gets an inside edge. The ball hits the pads and goes uppishly towards the leg side.
Shortish and outside off, it is punched through the off side but a single.
Good length ball angled into the batter, Crawley looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads. A muted appeal follows but dies down instantly.
Paterson starts with a length ball outside off, Sibley lets it be.
Outside off again, Sibley leaves it alone again.
Make that third leave as Paterson bowls it on a length and outside off.
FOUR! Width offered and Sibley pounces on it. It is slightly short and outside off, Sibley goes on the back foot and punches it through backward point for a boundary.
Length ball around off, it is defended.
Outside off this time, Sibley lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball angled into the batter, Crawley looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads.
Full ball on off, pushed towards mid on for a single.
Outside off, left alone.

OUT! Caught down the leg side! An excellent catch from de Kock and Hendricks has a Test wicket. He bowls it short one which is going down the leg side. Sibley looks to glance it towards fine leg but gets a faint tickle which goes behind. De Kock flies to his left and pouches the ball with his right hand. South Africa have broken the opening stand.
Outside off, left alone.
Another length ball outside off, Denly makes another leave.
Shortish ball outside off, Crawley slaps it to deep cover for a single.
In the channel outside off this time, Denly makes his third leave in as many balls.
He is off the mark now as Paterson bowls it on middle and on a length. Denly works it to deep square leg and takes a run.
Length ball angled in, Crawley flicks it to deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
Length ball around off, it is blocked.
Full ball on middle, it is stroked to mid on.
Brilliant bouncer from Hendricks once again. It is on the body. Crawley takes his eyes off and looks to sway away but the ball comes into him and hits him on the arms.
FOUR! Another bouncer from Hendricks and this time Crawley nails the pull powerfully! It goes to the deep mid-wicket fence in a flash.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Short and around off again, Crawley easily pulls it to the man at deep square leg for a run.
WIDE! Bouncer on middle, Crawley ducks under it. It is wided by the umpire.
Shortish ball around off, it is angled into the batter again. Denly looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Bouncer on middle, Denly ducks under it.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! Crawley departs and he is livid with himself after getting off to such a good start. Back of a length ball just around off, it nips away just a bit. Crawley looks to have a poke at it but the ball goes off the outside edge towards first slip where Rassie van der Dussen takes a very good catch at chest height. It looked like Crawley was in two minds, whether to play at it or leave and that has caused his downfall. Both the openers now depart and South Africa have a real opening here.
Another back of a length delivery near the off pole line, Root defends.
Length ball just around off, Joe Root defends off the back foot.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
On the pads of Root, he works it behind square and takes a single to get off the mark.
Good length ball on middle and off, defended by Denly.
Good length ball on off, played towards cover and Root takes an easy single.
Ouch! Hit on the thumb! Back of a length ball on middle, Denly looks to defend but the ball hits his thumb and onto the ground.
Another ferocious delivery, back of a length and angling in. Denly looks to work it towards the leg side but the ball goes off the inside edge onto the thigh pad and rolls towards the leg side.
Good length ball on middle and off, defended by Denly.
Bouncer on middle and leg, Denly ducks under this one.
Fuller ball this time, on the middle pole line, pushed down towards the man at mid on.
Length ball outside off, played towards point.
Good length ball on the leg pole line, Root plays this one towards the man at mid-wicket off the back foot.
Length ball just outside off, played towards cover off the front foot for a single.
On middle and leg, defended from within the crease.

Wonderful drive! Back of a length ball on off, swinging away. Denly drives this one beautifully through the cover region off the back foot but the ball does not have the legs to cross the fence and the batters take three.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman back towards the bowler.

DROPPED! What an effort here by Pieter Malan! It has just about popped out but had that stuck, this would have been a blinder. Paterson bowls a full ball outside off, Denly looks to drive it through point but does so uppishly. Pieter Malan there, dives full stretch to his right, gets one hand on the ball, but the ball does not stick and pops out. What a catch that would have been. Denly survives and he will be looking to make the most of this.
Length ball on middle and leg, Denly looks to flick but is hit on the thigh pad.
The batsman does well to stand tall and play that short delivery.
Good length ball on the pads, Denly gets an inside edge on this one and the ball rolls towards fine leg. The batters take a single.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot towards third man. Two runs added to the total.
FOUR! Punched away! Back of a length ball outside off, Denly stands tall and punches this one through the cover region for a boundary.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side for a single.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Full ball on off, driven towards the man at cover.
Outside off, played towards deep point for one.
On the pads, flicked towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Full ball on off, played towards the man at mid off.
Another full ball outside off, played to the man at mid off again.
FOUR! Third ball on the trot which is full and outside off and this time Paterson pays for it as Denly drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
Length ball on off, played past the point fielder and the batters take a couple.
Bouncer on middle and leg, ducked under.

EDGED AND FOUR! How lucky can you get? Well, Denly certainly is very lucky. Length ball just outside off, Denly looks to play at it but does so outside the line of the delivery. The ball takes the inside edge of the bat and goes right above the leg pole and into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Nortje starts with a poor line as he bowls this length ball on the pads, Root flicks it to deep square leg and takes a run.

EDGY FOUR! Denly is riding on his luck right now! A full ball outside off, Denly comes forward and looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes past the second slip fielder. It races away to the fence.
Slightly shorter and around off, blocked towards covers.
Full ball on middle, pushed to mid on.

Dropped! Another chance goes abegging! A short ball on middle, Denly rocks on the back foot and pulls it powerfully. The ball goes to Pretorius at mid-wicket very quickly. Pretorius jumps and looks to catch but the ball touches  his fingertips and goes to deep mid-wicket. A couple of runs.
Outside off, left alone.
On the pads on a length, it is worked to fine leg for a single.

OUT! Caught! Denly is not going to survive this time. Paterson has his first. A length ball just outside off, it pitches and then moves away. Denly has a poke at it with hard hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes straight to Rassie van der Dussen at first slip. He is not going to miss it out. He pouches it safely and Denly finally runs out of his luck. A very good phase for the hosts.
Outside off, Stokes lets it go to the keeper.
Another length ball outside off, Stokes again shoulders arms.
Stokes is off the mark. Paterson makes him play this ball as he dishes it out on middle. Stokes nudges it behind square leg and takes a single.
Full and on middle, it is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball just around off, Root leaves this one alone.
Good length ball on middle and off, defended towards the man at mid off.
Bouncer on middle and leg, ducked under.
Length ball just outside off, played towards point.
Back of a length ball outside off, left alone by Root. Bowled at a speed of 149 kph! Fierce!

EDGED AND FOUR! Back of a length ball just outside off, Root ducks and looks to leave that ball. However, it stays low and hits the top edge of Root's bat. It flies over the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Full length ball on the off pole line, defended towards the man at mid on.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Bouncer outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, Stokes lets it be.
Full ball on middle and off, played towards the man at mid on for a single. With this single, he gets to 1000 runs against the Proteas in Test matches.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! And it is the big fish, Ben Stokes, who has been dismissed! A full length ball outside off, angling away from Stokes. He looks to go for the drive away from his body but the ball goes off the outside edge towards the gap at first slip and second slip. Rassie van der Dussen takes another catch as he moves to his left. This is the wicket that the South Africans really wanted and Nortje has provided this crucial breakthrough.
Full ball on off, driven towards cover.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Good length ball on middle and off, played towards mid on.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Off the mark in style! Full ball on the middle and leg pole line, Pope flicks it nonchalantly through the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Outside off, played towards the point region for a single.
Full ball just outside off, played towards the man at mid off.
Good length ball just outside off, Pope makes a nice leave.
Length ball on the hips, worked towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Back of a length ball on off, Root pulls this one through the square leg region for a boundary.
Full ball on off, driven towards the man at mid off.
Good length ball on off, defended out.
FOUR! What a shot! Full ball just near the off pole line, Pope drives this one straight back past the bowler and into the fence down the ground. Signs of a man in supreme touch.
Outside off, left alone.
Full ball on off, driven towards the cover region where Pieter Malan does well to keep it down to two as he slides and saves the ball from reaching the fence.
On the pads, worked towards square leg for a single.
Good length ball on the off pole line, defended towards the man at cover and the batters take a quick single.
Good length ball angled into the batsman. It keeps a bit low there. Root does well to block it out.
Outside off, Root shoulders arms now.
Shortish and just outside off, Root rides the bounce and taps it through point for a single.
Angled into the batsman from middle and leg, Pope looks to tuck it around the corner but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards square leg and the batters cross over for a leg bye.
Full and around off, Root watchfully defends it under his eyes.
Full again but it is on the pads of Root. He flicks it to deep mid-wicket and runs for a brace.
In the channel outside off, Pope lets it go to the keeper.
On a length and just outside off, Pope pushes it towards the off side.
Landed on a length and around off, Pope lunges and defends it onto the pitch.
Another length ball around off, Pope pushes it towards covers.
Short of a length ball just outside off, Pope is cramped for room but he does well to cut it towards the man in the deep. A single taken.
Good length ball on off, Root keeps it out.
Hendricks starts with a full ball on off, it is defended.
Length ball angled in, it is worked towards mid-wicket for a run.
Another ball which is angled in from outside off, Root tucks it towards wide of the man at mid on for a single.
Back of a length on middle, it goes down the leg side with the angle. Pope lets it be.
Short and outside off, Pope flays it through point for a single.
Shortish and around off, it is defended.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Landed on middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
Full and just outside off, it is stroked through covers for a run.
Outside off on a length, Root lets it be.
Full ball on off and middle, driven to mid on.

Oops! Inside edge and straight into the delicate area! A length ball around off, Root looks to defend but gets an inside edge which goes between his legs and to fine leg. Root looks in pain but completes the run. He keeps running in the attempt of giving himself some time to get relieved.
On middle, pushed to mid-wicket.
Shortish and outside off, punched towards point for a single.
FOUR! Hendricks bowls a back of a length ball but it goes down the leg side. Pope just glances it fine down the leg side and it races away to the fence.
Another back of a length ball on the body, Pope somehow manages to squirt it away to the leg side. There is leg slip and a short leg in place for such chances.
What a bouncer! It is angled into the batter from outside off. Pope does really well to sway away from the firing line. Falls down in the process but one can say that he played this one really well.
Shortish and around off, Pope taps it to deep point for a single.
Extremely full ball on the off pole line, blocked out.
Good length ball now, defended back towards the bowler.
Fuller ball on the off pole line, played towards the man at mid on.
Fuller and around off, Pope defends it out.
Short and just outside off, Pope stays on the back foot and cuts it to deep point for a run.
Full ball on middle, Root flicks it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and around off, Pope comes forward and makes a solid block.
Angled into the pads, Pope looks to flick but misses.
The first ball of the day is around the wicket and Pope tucks it between short leg and leg gully for a single to fine leg.
Signs of swing. This one comes into the right-hander and Root misses his flick. Is hit in the pads and there are mild appeals for LBW but the angle was taking it down the leg side.

That is short and outside off, Root leaps and looks to play the upper cut. But he mistimes it really badly, not as if ever you could mistime any sweetly. Luckily for him, there is no one at point and by the time backward point gets across, the ball lands safely. Two runs taken.
Down the leg side, Root misses his flick.
Full and just around off, watchfully defended.
Around off, watchfully defended.
This is full and just around off, watchfully defended.
FOUR! That is a cracking shot. Fractionally short in length, outside off, Pope goes back and cuts it behind gully. Finds the boundary!
Landed outside off, watchfully left alone.
Full and outside off, the outswinger, allowed to pass.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Outside off, on a length, angling away, let through to the keeper again.
Make that three leaves in a row.
A bouncer now, sharp aggression, ducked under.
A length ball, outside off, coming in with the angle, watchfully defended.
Oohhh... that was very close! On a good length, around off, Pope came forward to defend but the ball jagged back off the seam, hit the front pad, then the right groin.
This is close too! Much fuller than the previous one, Ollie looks to defend but misses and is hit on the pads. Was there an inside edge?
Philander now goes the fullest, perfect length to get the LBW. But the line is a bit too straight. Flicked towards fine leg for a couple.
Around off, solidly defended.
Landed outside off, played through point for a single.
A length ball around off, Root stays back and defends.

FOUR! Are South Africa a host of some of the quickest scoring grounds in the world? Has to be. Once the runs come, they come at a thick rate. Short and outside off, Pope cuts it behind point for a boundary!
Full on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
This is just around off, solidly defended.
Back of a length outside off, pushed towards point.

Ben Laughlin for Australia. Manish Pandey for India. Temba Bavuma for South Africa. These people should be there in the team just for fielding. Outside off, Root punches this towards point and calls for a single. But Pope is not sure. He hesitates but eventually takes off for the run. Bavuma charges in to the ball from backward point, dives and then throws it sideways, at the striker's end, with every inch of his body in the air. Ollie Pope dives to save himself. Anyone remembering David Warner here? He would certainly remember the way he was run out by Bavuma. The replays show that even in the case of a direct hit, the full length dive would have saved Ollie.
Full and down the leg side, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
A good length around off, watchfully defended.
Fuller in length, just around off, watchfully defended, this time off the front foot.
There comes the fuller length again, well blocked out.
Tentative. A length ball, outside off, Root initially looks to defend but at the last moment, takes his bat away.

That is a good solid front foot defense. An in-form Root, or a Root in good touch would be confident about getting bat on ball, getting himself right behind the ball. A struggling Joe would be a bit twitchy, fidgeting around, looking to feel bat on every ball that is bowled and playing and missing. The Root we are seeing now, looks to be the former one. Good signs for England.
Around off, again Root gets right behind it to defend.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.

IN THE AIR... JUST WIDE! FOUR! Almost hit it down the throat. A short ball, outside off, Pope throws his bat at it, getting it over point. Now, there is Dane Paterson stationed in the deep at point. He starts just a second late and that costs him. Races to his left and then dives but the ball eludes him. Had he not taken that extra second to judge, he could have taken a well-judged catch. The Wanderers can be a difficult ground to sight the ball.
A bouncer now, Pope ducks.
This stays low, around middle, Ollie flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Full and outside off, this is driven through the covers for a couple.
Down the leg side, nudged towards fine leg leg or a run.
Outside off, Root pushes it with soft hands to the off side and scampers through for a single.

JUST SHORT OF SLIP! But why is he standing so deep? On second thoughts, that probably did not hit the edge at all. Yes. Replay confirms. A length ball, around off, Pope looks to defend but the ball moves away and squares him up. Goes off his right thigh and lands short of Rassie van der Dussen at first slip.
FOUR! HANDSOME! Overpitched from Nortje and Pope drives this straight down the ground. Beats mid on comfortably.
Pushes this through mid on for a single.
A tad short, Root hops and punches it through point for a run.
Around middle, helped through square leg for one.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
Around off, solidly defended.
This is let through to the keeper.

That is a shot which needs to be put away inside the locker. And Joe Root understands that. Hence he immediately turns away, hitting the air with his bat in frustration. A length ball outside off, Root gets across and taps it down to gully. A typical one-day shot, not needed here.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
That is in the air but well short of fine leg. A short ball, around middle, Pope swivels and pulls it in the air. Lands well in front of fine leg. A run taken.

A short ball, now Root pulls the ball away for a single. We have a delayed call for a no ball here. Umpire Joel Wilson at cover-point spots three men behind square on the leg side - a backward square leg, a fine leg and now, the man who is standing behind short leg is to the other side of the line. As per the rules, you can have only two men behind square on the leg side in any format. For all guys in T20 mode, the next delivery WILL NOT be a FREE HIT.

FOUR! Stylish way to get to a half century! A short ball, around off, Pope swivels and pulls it through square leg for a boundary! The in-form man gets his third 50-plus score of this series! Coming on the back of a splendid 132, on the back of an unbeaten 61 and do not forget - a 135 not out in the warm-up game as well. England have found their new Ian Bell / Joe Root.
On middle and leg, flicked through fine leg but short backward square leg dives to his left to stop.
On middle, pushed through to long on for a single.
TOP EDGE, SAFE! Would you believe it? A short ball, outside off, Root looks to pull but gets a top edge. The ball is in the air but does not carry to deep mid-wicket. A run taken.
Bouncer! The batsman does well to evade it.
Full and outside off, solidly defended.
Outside off, Root looks to defend but gets a bottom edge.
FOUR! Short and outside off, Root lashes out a cut shot and gets it past a diving point fielder for a boundary.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Short and outside off, pulled to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short again, outside off, cut straight to point.
Oohhh.... a short ball outside off, Root looks to punch but the ball rises suddenly and beats the outside edge.

FOUR! That is a controlled pull shot. That is a very short boundary too. Cannot imagine a shorter boundary in Test cricket, including Auckland and Wellington. A short ball, around middle, Root pulls this through mid-wicket and finds the boundary. With such small boundaries, all you need is put bat to ball and give it direction.
Full on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Works this through mid-wicket for a run.
Outside off, a half volley, driven straight to cover.

FOUR! Aha... classic Root. But the Saffas might as well have a fly slip in place if they are going to bowl that line and length. A short ball, outside off, coming in, Root arches back and then deftly ramps it over first slip to the third man fence!
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Down the leg side, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR LEG BYES! Badly lined. Full and down the leg side, Root misses his flick but the ball takes the pad and deflects to the fine leg fence.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle and leg, flicked straight to square leg.

Full and around middle, driven through mid on for a couple. THAT IS RUN NUMBER 50 FOR JOE ROOT in this innings. Please stand up and pat your back if you realized this was happening. Because we didn't. This is not a snooze fest but so many runs are coming and the two batsmen are so similar that it is hard to understand who is actually scoring. 47th Test fifty for the record!
Outside off, punched towards cover.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
Outside off, steered through point for a run.

100-RUN STAND IS UP! Yes, this everyone realized was coming. It has hardly been an hour since the two have been batting this morning, but it seems like they have batting for the last two days. Outside off, short in length, Pope arches back and steers it behind point for a run.

A huge shout for an LBW but it is turned down. Too high, perhaps. A length ball, around off, Pope looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. A closer look reveals that the ball bounced, took the elbow and hit the pads.
Fuller in length, around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Short and outside off, cut through point for a single.

That is a nice outswinger. Full and outside off, Root looks to drive but the ball swings away and beats the outside edge. When you move the ball, you can trouble the best of the best, even in the best of their form.

OUT! Pope drags it on! Drinks break followed by a fall of wicket, how many times have we seen that? Plenty for sure. Nortje provides the much-needed breakthrough for the Saffas this morning. He dishes out a full length delivery outside off at 144 kph, it lands and skids straight on as Pope decides to make a leave. But he keeps his bat hanging out there needlessly and the ball catches the inside half before destroying the stumps. Anrich becomes rich by one more wicket in Tests and South Africa will be relieved to see Ollie's back. That little bit of indecision has cost him his wicket and a golden chance to score back-to-back hundreds.
Hurls a good length delivery in the channel outside off, it's left alone by Jos.
Yet another speedy delivery, it's in the zone outside off and Buttler has nothing to do with it.
This one is closer to the off pole, fuller in length, Buttler pushes it to covers.

FOUR! That's a terrific way to get off the mark! Not a half-volley, it's proper length but with plenty of width outside off, Buttler takes his front leg forward and smashes it through covers. He has not been in good form of late and this shot will make him feel a lot better about himself.
Close to off, on a length, Buttler strokes it from the front foot to covers. End of a successful over for South Africa!
Root has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Around middle, Root plays it with the angle and taps it down to mid-wicket.
Lands it full and outside off, Root presses forward and pushes it with gentle hands through cover-point. They pick up a single.
A hint of away shape on this delivery but the line is quite wide outside off to bother the batsman.
This one is on a driving length around off, once again a lovely shape away from the batsman, Buttler covers his stumps and allows it through.
Yet another watchful leave by Buttler to round off the over.
Good length close to off, Root stays back-footed and taps it down to backward point.

Spears in a very full ball on middle at 142 kph, Root falls across a bit as he pushes it out to mid on. The ground is now bathed in sunshine and it's looking like great conditions, especially for batting.
Very full and straight again by Nortje, Root flicks it on the leg side but finds mid-wicket.
Good length ball around off, Root is solidly behind the line in defense.
Clocks 144 kph and sends across a speedy short delivery just outside off. Root drops his wrists and leans back to evade it. Wears a smile after that as Anrich gives him a stare.

DROPPED BY DU PLESSIS! Poor Anrich Nortje. He is amidst a great spell and has the rhythm going and would have struck twice after the Drinks break but his skipper lets him down. After delivering a heavy last ball, he serves it on a length around off. Root has a gentle push inside the line, sans any footwork, and gets a healthy outside edge to wide first slip. Faf moves across to his right swiftly, pouches the ball at first but then it pops out. Du Plessis is frustrated but spare a thought for this young bowler. He's giving his all in this spell and needs support from his teammates.
Full and around off, swinging in late, flicked nicely but straight to short mid-wicket.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Full and around off, Faf is solid in defense.
Pitches it up around off, Root pushes it down towards mid on for a run.
Good length ball around off, Buttler punches it off his back foot to covers.

BEATEN! It's all happening after the Drinks break. Pretorius gets a length ball to move considerably off the pitch. Buttler is forward to push it through the line but it nips back in and beats the inside edge. Excellent passage of play for the Saffas. Just need some luck to get on top!
Fullish and straightish, pushed down to mid on with a straight bat.
A length delivery outside off, Root forces it off his back foot but finds extra cover. The fielder makes a half stop.

FOUR! Just uses the extra pace of the bowler. A 146 kph delivery, short and outside off, Root arches back and ramps it over first slip. It drops once and then crosses the fence. Good battle between these two!
Play and a miss this time. On a length and around off, shaping away, Root pokes inside the line, once again flat-footed, and misses.

OUT! Caught behind! Nortje gets his man this time. The speed merchant wins his battle with one of the best Test batsmen going around. Probing line from him and Root falls prey. Lack of footwork once again shown by the English skipper and that has brought his downfall. Anrich clocks 143 kph and serves it on a length close to off. It shapes away a bit late. Root has a needless poke inside the line and gets a fat outside edge behind. Quinton de Kock stretches to his right and grabs the catch safely. Anrich smiles.

OUT! Nortje is on fire. What did he consume at the Drinks break? Breathing fire in his bowling spell and has brought South Africa back in with a shout in this match. A delivery which has been served on a fuller length outside off. Curran flashes his bat at it but only manages to edge a 145 kph ball. One thing was again missing - Footwork! A healthy edge is gobbled by Quinton de Kock and this is now Nortje's best effort in Test cricket. Take a bow, young man! What a spell! This will truly be the stepping stone of his Test career. We will have to wait to see his hat-trick ball as this splendid over has come to a close.
Full and outside off, some away movement from the right-hander, Buttler shoulders arms.
Around off, worked off the inner half towards short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
Landed outside off, more outswing, let through.
Full and outside off, gently placed to cover.
Landed outside off, another one let through to the keeper.
Left alone. No hat-trick. It's a length delivery in the channel outside off, Woakes covers his stumps and has an easy leave.
Excellent lines once again from Anrich. Delivers it on a length close to off and it skids on after landing, Chris shoulders arms.
Bowls it in the line of the stumps, on a good length, Woakes gets behind the line and pushes it to mid on.
It's been driven superbly through the covers. They pick up a single. Woakes opens his account.
Arrows in a full ball on middle, a bit of reverse movement in the air, Buttler flicks it in front of square leg for a run.
Back of a length ball on off, Chris sticks on the back and defends it back to the bowler.
Pitches it up and outside off, Buttler leans on the front foot and drives it to mid off.
Too full around off, Buttler brings down a straight bat in defense.

FOUR! Off the inside half! Fuller length ball on middle and shaping down, Buttler gets forward to flick it through mid-wicket but it catches the inner half and races fine down the leg side for a boundary.
This time it's an outswinger outside off, Buttler allows it through to the keeper.
Inside edge again! Fullish and close to off, moving off the deck, Buttler tries to unfurl an off drive but gets a fat inside edge onto the pads.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
FOUR! Crunched! Fullish delivery around off, Woakes drives it straight down the ground. Excellent timing and it first beats the bowler and then mid off for a glorious boundary.
Shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Movement off the deck again. Hendricks delivers it full and close to off, Woakes gets forward to block but it takes the inside edge and strikes him on the pads.
This time the line is straight, Woakes uses the angle of the bowler and tucks it behind square leg for one.
Short delivery in the line of the stumps, Buttler eases it from the crease to long leg for a single.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Buttler remains on the back foot and dabs it down in front of gully.
Fullish and around off, Jos presses forward and drives it to mid off.
A gentle delivery, on a fuller length around off at 126 kph, Buttler defends it from the toe end of his bat to mid on.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Fuller length ball around off, at 77 mph, Buttler falls over a bit as he tries to flick. It goes slightly uppishly but safely to mid-wicket.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat. Maiden!
Hendricks begins this over from over the wicket. Serves a good length ball around leg, Woakes goes back and eases it to the right of mid on for a run.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Buttler rocks back and cuts it through point for a single.
Digs it short and just outside off, Woakes sways away from the line.
Fuller length ball on middle and off, Woakes defends it from the crease.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Chris stays back and taps it down to mid-wicket.
Once again Woakes works a length ball on the leg side but finds mid-wicket.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman. They pick up a single.
A tempter by Pretorius. It's on a fuller length outside off, there to be driven, Woakes shows good patience as he makes a leave.

Pretorius gets close to the off stump line and forces the batsman to play at it. Woakes tries to flick and gets it away off the inner half. It rolls in front of square leg and they cross for a couple of times.

FOUR! Poor start with the new nut. Too straight and full, Woakes picks it off his pads and clips it through mid-wicket. Good timing and it races away to the fence in no time. The hard ball will come onto the bat nicely too.
Woakes has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Slightly short and around off, Woakes once again gets an inside edge and it goes behind square leg for a run.
A length ball on middle and off, Woakes defends it from the crease.
Beaten this time. Hendricks takes a full length ball away from the right-hander. Woakes stays back to push inside the line but is beaten by the angle of the bowler.

FOUR! Not in control but still a boundary. Hendricks pitches it up and around off, nipping away a shade, Woakes tries to unveil a cover drive but it takes the outer half of his blade and spears through point for a boundary.
Inside edge this time. On a length around off, Woakes brings his bat down to defend but it takes the inside edge and goes towards square leg for a run.

EDGY FOUR! Unfortunate for South Africa. This new nut is leaking runs. A length delivery in the zone outside off, Buttler pushes inside the line with soft hands and gets a thick outside edge. It though falls short and wide of second slip before speeding behind for a boundary at third man. 300 up for England!
Another delivery in the channel outside off, this time Buttler shows respect and allows it through. LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Starts with a good length delivery outside off, shaping away, Woakes allows it through to the keeper.
Pitches it up and around middle, Woakes flicks it from the inner half through backward square leg for a run.
The length is very full again, it's on middle, Buttler pushes it down off his pads to mid on.
Half the bat there! Philander serves it on a fuller length on off, Buttler slices his attempted cover drive to deep point for a couple of runs.
Good leave. On a length around off, shaping in a bit, Buttler trusts the bounce and shoulders arms. It goes over the stumps.
Fullish ball on off, it's driven to extra cover where the fielder makes a half stop and parries it to mid off.
Full in length and outside off, at 142 kph, Woakes needlessly hangs his bat out and gets beaten.
Angles into the batsman, Woakes gets forward and pushes it to mid on.

Shortish delivery on middle and leg, Woakes initially shapes up to glance it across the line but is caught in an awkward point. He somehow stays back inside the crease and avoids the ball by taking evasive action.
Clocks 146 kph this time, Woakes shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Too full and on middle, speared into the batsman, Woakes keeps it out to mid on.
FOUR! Good timing and placement! A length delivery around middle, Woakes turns inside the crease and eases it with good timing through mid-wicket for a boundary.
False shot! Back of a length delivery outside off, shaping away off the seam, Buttler sticks back to punch it through the line but misses.
Angles in a good length ball on middle, Buttler covers the line and bunts it towards mid on.
Easy pickings! Shortish and around leg, Jos nudges it to fine leg where Nortje moves across to his right to make the stop. They manage to come back for the second.
Stays back-footed to a shortish ball and pushes it to covers.

OUT! That's a tremendous catch! Never easy to run back and catch those. Well done, Dean Elgar. Philander has his second scalp and the crowd just loved it. Buttler tries to dominate the bowler by giving him the charge. It's a shortish length delivery outside off at 125 kph, Jos shimmies down the track to muscle it across the line but gets a thick top edge. It flies in the air at covers where Elgar runs back, keeps his eyes on the ball and pouches the skier safely. Buttler has thrown away his wicket and South Africa will be relieved that this partnership didn't hurt them much. Can they now restrict England under 325?
On a good length outside off, Woakes shoulders arms. A successful over for Vernon!
A bouncer but down the leg side, Wood ducks.
On a length outside off, Mark plays inside the line but the ball shapes away to beat the outside edge.
Full and straight, watchfully defended.
A length ball now, watchfully defended.
Back of a length outside off, defended with a leap.
Another solid forward defense to end the over.
Full on middle, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Fuller in length, well blocked out.
Full and outside off, driven wide of cover for a single.
Around off, well blocked out.
EDGE, DID IT CARRY? Nope. Full and outside off, Wood looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge. Does not quite carry to Faf du Plessis at second slip.
Around off, blocked from the crease.
FOUR! Nicely done. Full on middle, Woakes flicks it through mid-wicket and finds the boundary.
Outside off, played through point for a single.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
A bouncer now, Mark ducks.
A length ball, down the leg side, helped through square leg for a run.
Full and outside off, played straight to point.
Outside off, on a length, Wood plays inside the line but the ball straightens and beats the outside edge.
A length ball, around off, well defended.
A terrific yorker on middle and off, Mark just about digs it out.
Landed outside off, let through.
Landed outside off again, on a length, MW feels for it but is beaten.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Half volley outside off, driven straight to mid off.

OUCH. That hurts. Thankfully, Woakes is okay. A length ball outside off, Chris looks to defend initially but then takes his eyes off the ball. Looks to fend it but the ball pings him on his gloves and then hits him on his body.
Outside off, Chris gets it through point for a couple of runs.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.

OUT! Edged and this time Faf du Plessis has taken the catch! MAIDEN TEST 5-FER FOR ANRICH NORTJE. South Africa have had very few moments to celebrate in this series and this is one of them. A length ball, outside off, Woakes looks to drive but all he manages is a thick outside edge. The ball flies slightly wide of first slip where Faf du Plessis takes it nicely to his right.
Landed outside off, played straight to point.
On middle and leg, helped through mid-wicket for a couple.

Full and outside off, Wood hammers this powerfully back. Paterson tries sticking his right hand out but the ball whizzes past his hand and hits the stumps at the other end. The ball deflects towards cover and a single is taken.
A bouncer, Broad ducks.
There comes the full ball, Stuart backs away and swings hard. Just about manages to get his bat down in time and the ball goes off the inside edge, towards fine leg. A single taken.

SIX! SLAUGHTERED! That is an extraordinary shot from Wood. A short ball, outside off, Wood backs away, picks the slower ball and then smashes it over cover. There is a man stationed at sweeper but it flies over him!
A length ball outside off, angling away, Broad plays inside the line and is beaten.
A short ball outside off, Stuart flashes hard but misses.
FOUR! STUPENDOUS! That is the Stuart Broad we all know! A length ball outside off, Broad backs away and slams it over cover!
This time he stays on the back foot and meekly pushes at the ball. Gets an outside edge, through the vacant gully position to third man. A single taken.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Backs away down the leg side, Nortje follows him, Wood swings hard but only gets an inside edge onto his pads.
A short ball outside off, Broad swings but misses.

SIX! That is a fabulous shot from Broad. So fabulous that the umpire has to raise both his arms in the air. A length ball outside off, Broad swings this through the line and lofts it as clean as a whistle over long off!
A short ball, outside off, Stuart goes for the hook but is beaten.
The batsman fails to put bat on ball.
Gets a top edge now. A short ball, SB looks to hook but gets a top edge. However, the ball lands in no man's land near mid-wicket. Two runs taken.

SIX! SMASH! Broad, o Broad, o Broad... where were you all these months? Broad is doing horrible damage to South Africa here. He has raced to 20 from just 12 balls, with 16 of those coming in boundaries! A short ball, outside off, Broad goes deep in his crease and hooks this over square leg!
FOUR! That is squeezed away! Tail-end torture from England. Full and outside off, Wood just about gets his bat down in time to eke it past gully to the third man fence!
FOUR! Up and over! Clean hitting. Full and around middle, Wood backs away and swings this over mid on for a boundary!
SIX! SMOKED! It is raining boundaries at the Bull Ring. A short ball now, Wood backs away and heaves. The connection is excellent and the ball sails over mid-wicket!
Outside off, on a length, Wood slashes hard but misses.
Swing and a miss! Length ball outside the off stump line, Wood looks to heave it away but fails to get any bat on it.
Short delivery on middle, Wood pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
EDGY! Full delivery outside off, Wood looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and goes towards third man. A single taken.
Yorker! It is bowled outside off, Broad looks to drive but misses.
SIX! Amazing piece of hitting! Full ball on middle, Broad hammers it over the bowler's head for a biggie. 50-run partnership is up between the two. Adding crucial runs for their side.
Yorker outside off, Broad attempts to drive but fails to get any bat on it.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around off, Broad looks to hook but misses it altogether.
EDGY! Full delivery on off, Broad looks to drive but it takes the inside edge and rolls to square leg. The batter takes a single.
Good length delivery down the leg side, Broad hops to flick but misses it.
Back of a length ball on off, Broad taps it towards the point region for a single.
WIDE! Short delivery way outside off, Wood moves a bit to the off side and then looks to cut but misses. The umpire signals it a wide.
Yorker on middle, Wood digs it out towards square leg for a single.
Fullish delivery outside off, Broad looks to drive but the ball takes the inside half of the bat and goes towards long on. A single taken.
Short of a length delivery outside off, Wood rocks on his back foot to pull but fails to make any connection with it.
Shorter delivery outside off, Wood sways away from it. Frustration continues for South Africa.
Very full delivery on middle, Broad pushes it down to long off for a single.
BEATEN! Slower length delivery outside off, Wood looks to drive but the ball whizzes past the outside edge of the bat and goes into the mitts of the keeper.

Yorker on middle, Wood gets his bat down in time and digs it out. It hits his back pad and goes towards square leg. A single taken. The fielders from the slip cordon appeal but the umpire is not interested.
Paterson dishes a full ball on middle, Broad heaves it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Wood ducks under it.
Full delivery on middle, Wood defends it back to the bowler.
SIX! Short ball on off, Broad camps on the back foot and pulls it with disdain to the deep square leg region for a biggie.
Just short! Slower delivery on middle, Broad does not hard on his pull and just paddles it. The ball lands in front of the deep square leg fielder. The batters take a single.
Good length ball outside off, Wood punches it to deep cover for a single.
FOUR LEG BYES! This is poor bowling! Full toss down the leg side, Broad looks to flick but misses it. The ball goes off the thigh pad and into the fine leg fence.
Short ball on off, Broad looks to pull but it takes the top edge and the ball goes towards deep mid-wicket. A single taken.
SIX! Hammered! Full delivery outside off, Wood thrashes it over the deep cover region for a biggie.
FOUR! What placement from Broad and it brings up 400 in style. Short ball on middle, Broad whacks the pull towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, South Africa have broken through. What a partnership this was for England! They were not looking like they will reach 400 but Wood and Broad have propelled them to that. Short ball on middle, Broad looks to pull but the ball takes the top edge. It goes up in the air and goes towards deep square leg. Malan stationed there settles himself and takes the catch. Some relief for the Proteas. ENGLAND HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 400.
Broad starts with a good length ball outside off. The ball has some bounce on it but Elgar is not disturbed as he leaves the ball alone.
Full delivery outside off, Elgar leaves the ball alone.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Elgar looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. There is a stifled appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar lets the ball through to the keeper.
On a length outside off, nipping away from the batsman. Elgar makes another leave.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar shoulders arms to this one. Maiden to start with from Broad.
Full delivery outside off, swinging into the batsman. Malan spots that and then makes a leave to the ball after covering his stumps.
Length ball on middle and leg, Malan works it to square leg.
South Africa are underway! Fullish delivery on middle, angling in. Malan whips it to backward square leg for a single.
Elgar is underway! Length ball on off, Elgar taps it towards the point region and takes a single.
BEATEN! Beautiful bowling from Curran. Length ball outside off, going away from the batsman. Malan looks to defend off the front foot but gets beaten.
Length ball outside off, Pieter lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery outside off, Elgar leaves the ball alone to the keeper.
Back of a length ball outside off, Elgar shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery down the leg side, Elgar looks to flick it but fails to get any bat on it.
Length ball outside off, Dean shoulders arms to this one.
On a length on the pads, Elgar whips it to square leg.
Down the leg side, Elgar looks to flick but fails to get any bat on it.
Full delivery on middle, Pieter pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery on the pads, Malan works it to square leg for nothing.
Length ball outside off, moving into the batsman, Malan shoulders arms but gets hit on the body. No harm done though.
Fullish delivery on off, Malan looks to defend but get hit on the pads.
On off, defended towards the point region.
Very full delivery, shaping into the batsman. Malan gets his bat down in time and defends it out.
Good length ball on the pads, Elgar works it to fine leg for a single.
Length ball on middle, Pieter flicks it to backward square leg for a single.
Fullish delivery outside off, Dean does not fiddle with it and leaves the ball alone.
On a length on middle, Elgar looks to whip it to the leg side but gets hit high on the pads.
Fullish delivery down the leg side, Elgar attempts the flick but fails to get any bat on it.
BEATEN! Excellent bowling from Broad. Good length delivery around off, Elgar looks to defend but the ball sneaks between the bat and pad. Almost kissed the inside edge.
Short ball on middle, Malan pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Very full delivery on middle, Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery outside off, shaping away from the batter. Elgar shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length ball on middle, which straightens after pitching. Elgar stands tall and then defends it off the back foot.
Length ball outside off, Dean shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball down the leg side, Elgar attempts the flick shot but misses.
Length ball on off, Malan blocks it to point.
Good length ball, nipping back into the batsman. Malan attempts to defend but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Full delivery on middle, Malan pushes it back to the bowler.
Fullish ball outside off, Malan looks to drive but it takes the inside edge and goes onto hit the pads.
On the pads, worked to deep square leg for a single.
Full delivery outside off, Elgar pushes it to mid off.
Woakes starts with a good length ball on off, Malan stands tall and then defends it to point.
Length ball outside off, Pieter shoulders arms to this one.
Fullish ball outside off, Pieter has no problems in leaving this ball alone.
Full delivery outside off, Malan makes another leave.
Good length ball on off, Malan blocks it to short leg.
Full delivery on middle, Malan defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery outside off, moving in. Elgar shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Elgar defends it to point and takes off for a single. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Had he hit, it would have not mattered as the batter was in though.
Full delivery on middle, with some movement taking it down the leg side. Malan looks to flick but it takes the inside edge of the bat and goes towards fine leg for a single.
Length ball on off, Elgar defends it to point.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Elgar looks to defend off the back foot but the ball angles away and beats the outside edge of the bat.
Good length ball on middle, Malan defends it towards the leg side.
Fuller one outside off, Malan shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Beautiful piece of bowling! Length ball outside off, tailing away. Malan looks to defend but misses it altogether.
On middle, whipped to mid-wicket.
Full delivery outside off, Malan defends it to point.
Fullish delivery on middle, Pieter pushes it to mid on.
Short ball outside off, Elgar punches it off the back foot to cover and takes a single.
Fullish delivery outside off, Malan shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball on middle, Malan tucks it to short leg.
Good length ball on off, pushed to point.
Good length ball on middle, Malan defends it to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Malan works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Full delivery outside off, Malan lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Malan lunges forward and defends it out to point.
Fullish delivery on off, Malan looks to defend off the front foot  but it takes the inside edge and goes towards square leg. The batters take a single.
Full delivery outside off, Elgar shoulders arms to this one.
Play and a miss! Full delivery outside off, Elgar looks to drive but fails to get any bat on it.
Fullish delivery on middle, Elgar defends it out to the bowler. TEA ON DAY 2.
Length ball outside off, Malan shoulders arms to it.
Full and angled into middle, Malan pushes it to mid on.
Full and on middle, Malan looks to flick but it takes an inside edge and goes through square leg for a couple.
Length ball outside off, going away from Malan. He just lets it be.
On off, kept out.
Malan shoulders arms to this length ball outside off without any fuss.
BEATEN! Angled away from the left-hander. Woakes pitches on a length and around off, Elgar goes for a drive without any footwork only to get beaten on the outside edge.
Good length ball outside off, Left alone.
Length ball on off, Elgar taps it to point.
Length delivery on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Once again outside off and Elgar is happy to leave it.
Elgar is not tempted to play any ball outside off as he lifts his bat and lets the ball go through.
Outside off, Malan lets it be.
BEATEN! Wood angles the ball into Malan and then makes it to straighten it. Malan plays for the original line and gets beaten on the forward push.
Malan chooses not to fiddle with this length delivery outside off.
This time Wood makes Malan play by bowling close to off stump. Malan defends it to point off the front foot.

OUCH! That must have pinged Malan there. Back of a length ball on middle, It comes back into Malan. Pieter there looks to leave it by dropping his wrists but the ball hits his arm and rolls towards point.
Outside off, left alone.

EDGY FOUR! Elgar is lucky there to not edge it behind to the slips. He sees the width and goes for a drive only to get a thick outside edge as the ball flies past the vacant gully region. The ball had some extra bounce on it too as it raced to the fence for a boundary.
outside off, Elgar defends it off the back foot.

BEAUTY OF A DELIVERY! Elgar is completely squared up on this. Woakes bowls in the channel outside off and Elgar looks to defend but the extra bounce on the ball once again means that the ball goes past the outside edge.
Full and on off, pushed to mid-wicket.
Another delivery where the batsman gets beaten. Length ball outside off, Elgar looks to defend only to get beaten on the outside edge.
Second time in a row Elgar is beaten on the outside edge as he looks to defend this length ball.
Outside off, pushed to the off side off the back foot.
Once again Malan looks to leave the ball that is coming in and once again he is struck on the arm.
FOUR! Back of a length ball outside off, Malan throws the kitchen sink at it as he gets a top edge and the ball flies over the slip cordon and into the fence at third man for a boundary.
Malan now gets an inside edge on the defense. The ball goes past the short leg fielder and the batsmen manage to rotate the strke.

EDGED AND FOUR! Elgar is a lucky man there. He once again goes for the drive on this length ball outside off without any footwork and once again gets an inside edge on it. The ball goes past the stumps and falls just near the keeper who is diving to his right. The ball evades him and runs to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Short ball and Elgar ducks under it. The keeper there leaps in the air to collect it.
Full delivery on middle, Malan works it to short leg and takes off for a single. Woakes runs across, picks up the ball and throws it at the keeper's end. He misses.
Full delivery on off, Elgar pushes it back to Woakes who makes a half stop. The ball rolls towards mid on and the batters take a single.

BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Malan looks to defend but gets beaten. They appeal but the umpire is not interested. The English do not go for the review. Wait a minute, the Ultra Edge rolls in and it looks close. There is a spike on it. Not sure whether the ball has gone off the outside edge or the noise is off the bat hitting the pad.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Full delivery on middle, Malan defends it out to the bowler.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Good length and outside off, Elgar is not interested to play it.
Full and on middle, Elgar just pushes it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Malan is not going to fiddle with any delivery outside off as he shoulders arms once again.
Wood goes full and angles one into Malan and then straightens it. Malan looks to drive only to get a thick outside edge which falls just short of the man at gully.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally Wood's persistence pays off. He was constantly probing that line outside off and this time Malan cannot resist his instincts and pokes at a delivery which was leaving him. He gets a thick outside edge and goes to the keeper. Buttler there makes no mistake and starts celebrating. Wood is over the moon and why won't he be? Wood and England have been excellent after Tea.
Van der Dussen leaves this length delivery outside off to begin with.
BEATEN! Elgar is beaten on the outside edge for the umpteenth time in this innings. This time Stokes angles one away and Elgar looks to run it down only to miss it.
FOUR! On the pads and Elgar says thank you as he flicks this one through mid-wicket and the ball runs to meet the boundary cushions.
Outside off, left alone.
Once again outside off and Elgar leaves it for the keeper to do the rest.
FOUR! Length ball on off, Elgar looks to defend it off the back foot only to get an outside edge. The ball rolls past the second slip fielder and into the third man fence for another boundary.
On off, defended off the back foot.

Cracker of a nut there. He bowls one on a length and takes the ball away from Rassie. Van der Dussen looks to defend it from within the crease and has a feel for the ball as it sneaks past the outside edge.
Rassie leaves this length ball outside off alone.
Length ball on middle, Rassie drives it to mid on.
Rassie defends the length ball off the back foot.
Length delivery defend off the front foot towards mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! Curran into the wickets now. He was bowling superbly and was constantly hitting the hard length. This time he bowls a wobble-seam delivery on middle and gets a hint of away movement as Rassie looks to defend it off the back foot. The ball catches the shoulder of the bat and flies towards second slip where Stokes accepts the catch gleefully. South Africa's same old story continues.

EDGED AND FOUR! Elgar has really been lucky here! Edges has not gone to hand. Full delivery outside off, Elgar looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and the ball goes through the gully region for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone by Elgar.
Full delivery on middle, Elgar tucks it to  mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Elgar works it to the leg side.
Length ball outside off, Elgar looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Length ball outside off, Elgar shoulders arms to it.
Curran bowls one down the leg side and Faf lets it go through.
On middle and off, Faf defends it off the back foot to mid off.
Full and on middle, driven straight to the man at mid on.
Length ball on off, Faf defends it with the full face of the bat towards mid off.
Length ball on the pads, du Plessis flicks it off his hips towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
BEATEN! Elgar is facing the heat here. He gets beaten once again while poking at a length ball outside off.
Length delivery outside off, du Plessis defends it off the front foot towards cover.
Back of a length ball on off, Faf defends it towards mid on.

Stokes bowls one on a length and on middle and leg. The ball Faf looks to take evasive action but the ball hits his ribs and goes to fine leg fence. Since du Plessis was not offering any shot it is called as a dead ball.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot. One run added to the total.

OUT! CAUGHT! Soft dismissal for Elgar. Dean plays it irresponsibly to go back to the pavilion. Stokes goes short and wide outside off and Elgar goes to cut it uppishly. But he fails to clear the in-field and gives a simple catch to Chris Woakes at point. Completely uncharacteristic way to get out. South Africa reeling now!
Nasty! Good length ball on off, bouncing a little more than expected. De Kock looks to defend but gets hit on the gloves.
Back of a length ball on off, du Plessis defends it to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, du Plessis works it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length ball on the pads, du Plessis works it to square leg.
Full delivery outside off, du Plessis lets the ball go to the keeper.
On middle, whipped to mid-wicket.
On middle, Faf defends it solidly onto the pitch.
Full and on middle, de Kock flicks it through mid-wicket and gets off the mark with a couple.
Length and on middle, pushed to mid-wicket.
Short and outside off, Quinton leaves it alone.
Length ball on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball angled into de Kock pushes it off the back foot towards mid on.
FOUR! Shot that has been crunched. Stokes overpitches slightly around off and de Kock is quick to get on the front foot and drive it through covers for a boundary.
Length delivery outside  off, Faf does not fiddle with it.
Du Plessis defends this length ball off the back foot.
Full and on the pads, Faf flicks it towards fine leg and gets off strike.
FOUR! Back of a length ball outside off, de Kock cuts it late and goes through vacant gully for a boundary at third man.
Full ball on off, de Kock is happy to keep it out.
Full and on the pads, de Kock flicks it through square leg. The fielder from mid on and fine leg both run towards the ball and the latter runs across to his right to save a couple.
Full delivery outside off, du Plessis shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside off, du Plessis makes a leave to this one.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length ball outside off, Faf does not fiddle with it and leaves the ball alone.
Length ball on off, du Plessis defends it out to the bowler.
Full delivery outside off, Faf shoulders arms to this one.
Broad starts with a good length ball on off, de Kock defends it out.
FOUR! Whipped away nicely. Fullish ball on the pads, de Kock whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length ball on middle, de Kock defends it to mid on.
Fullish ball outside off, de Kock lets the ball go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller one outside off, de Kock shoulders arms.
Good length ball outside off, du Plessis shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, du Plessis defends it to mid on.
Full delivery on off, du Plessis lunges forward and blocks it to cover.
Good length ball on off, Faf solidly blocks it out.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call it is and du Plessis fails yet again. This is brilliant bowling from Woakes though. Good length ball on off. Gets the ball to come back into the batsman. Du Plessis looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. Woakes and the rest appeal and the umpire gives it out. Faf discusses with Quinton and goes for the review. Woakes is fine on the no ball front. The Ball Tracker then comes in and it shows that it is umpire's call on hitting the stumps. Review retained but they lose their skipper. Woakes deserves this wicket as he has been brilliant since he came into the attack. Can South Africa survive without losing any more wickets till Stumps?
