Full delivery outside off, Bavuma drives it through the cover region for three. The fielder chases after it and slides to make the stop.
Full and outside off, Bavuma drives it to point.
Back of a length and on middle, Bavuma defends it towards short leg.
Length ball outside off, Temba leaves it for the keeper to do the rest.
BEATEN! Nicely bowled by Broad there. He goes a bit fuller and swings away from the forward push of Bavuma. The ball goes past the outside edge.
Outside off, Bavuma leaves it.
Once again Bavuma is content with leaving the ball outside off.
Back of a length and on off, de Kock taps it towards point and looks for a single. He is sent back by his partner who is ball watching at the other end.
De Kock punches the ball off the back foot through covers and scampers for a single.
Good length and outside off, Bavuma plays it to point.
Length delivery outside off, Bavuma drops it in front of covers and takes off for a quick single.
FOUR! Beautiful timing on that. Full ball on middle, de Kock presents the full face of the bat and drives it past the bowler. The ball hurries towards the fence at long off for a boundary.
Outside off, punched off the back foot to the off side.
Length ball outside off, Bavuma taps it towards gully and gets to the other end.
Quinton drives this length delivery straight to mid off.
BEATEN! De Kock is lucky not to edge that one behind. He looks to defend this length ball outside off but the ball goes past the outside edge.
De Kock looks to drive this through the off side but gets it off the inside half of the bat towards mid-wicket.
Full ball on off, de Kock does well to dig it out.
Outside off, de Kock drives it only to find mid off.
Length ball around off, Bavuma compactly defends it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on off, angling into Bavuma, who hops and looks to fend it only to get hit on the belly.
Length delivery outside off, Bavuma is happy to let that go.
Good length and on off, Bavuma drives but not from the middle of the willow. He finds cover there.
Full delivery down the leg side, Bavuma looks to flick that but he misses it.
Outside off, pushed off the back foot towards point.
Length delivery outside off, de Kock drives it through covers for a run.
BEATEN! Length delivery swinging away. Bavuma looks to just punch it off the back foot. The ball further swings away and goes past the outside edge.
BRAVE LEAVE! Now, Broad brings one into the right-hander. Bavuma shoulders arms to it. The ball is not far away from kissing the off pole.
Bavuma leaves this length ball outside off for the keeper.
Bavuma drives this full ball towards covers and gets to the other end.
Full on the pads, de Kock flicks it through square leg and retains the strike.
BEATEN! De Kock  plays a rash shot only to not get an edge. Wood serves one on a length and outside off, de Kock frees his arms but fails to get wood on the ball.
Full and on the pads, de Kock flicks it to fine leg and goes to the other end.
Outside off, Bavuma lets it go.
Once again the batsman leaves it alone as it is outside off and not in his playing zone.
Bavuma lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Back of a length ball on middle, Bavuma hops inside the crease and defends it towards short leg.
Full and on middle, de Kock drives it straight to the man at mid on.
Length ball outside off, de  Kock decides to not touch it.
Short ball on off, de Kock does well to drop his wrists and sway away from the line of the delivery.
Length delivery angling away from Quinton, he lifts his bat and lets the ball through.
Another length ball outside off, de Kock is not interested to play at it.
Back of a length ball on off, de Kock defends it off his back foot towards the slip cordon.
BEATEN! Short ball outside off, Bavuma attempts the cut but fails to get any bat on it.
Full delivery outside off, Temba shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball on middle, Bavuma looks to defend but get hit near the box.

OUT! CAUGHT! Stokes has collected it cleanly and Bavuma has to make his way back to the pavilion. Short of a length ball on off, Bavuma looks to defend off the back foot but gets an outside edge towards second slip. Ben Stokes lunges forward and takes the catch. He gets up and starts celebrating. Bavuma is not going anywhere as he is not sure that it is a clean catch. The umpires want to check and they go upstairs. The soft signal is out. The replays roll in and they show that Stokes had his fingers underneath the ball. South Africa keep on crumbling.
FOUR! Nice way to get off the mark. Full delivery on the pads, Nortje flicks it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Full ball outside off, de Kock pushes it towards long off and takes a single.
Short ball on off, well-directed one too. Nortje hops and defends it awkwardly towards short leg, where it just falls short of Ollie Pope.
Another back of a length ball on off, Nortje once again is surprised as he defends it in a confused way.
Outside off, Anrich leaves it alone.
Nortje now drives this full ball through mid on and gets a couple.
Length ball outside off, Nortje lets it be.
Full ball outside off, de Kock drives it through covers. The ball will not reach the fence as there is protection out there. The batsmen are content with a single.
Back of a length ball on off, Nortje hops and defends it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery outside off, Nortje chooses not to play at it.
Back of a length ball around off, Nortje looks to defend it to the off side but the ball bounces a tad more and goes past the outside edge as Anrich hops to block it.
Length ball down the leg side, Nortje looks to flick it to the leg side but fails to get ball on ball.
Length ball on off, defended  off the back foot.
De Kock pushes this full ball on middle back to the bowler.
FOUR! Short ball on middle and leg, de Kock just helps it on his way through fine leg and the ball runs to the fence.
Length delivery on off, driven towards mid off for a single.
Nortje blocks the ball off the back foot towards mid on.
Once again, Nortje defends it to mid on.
Full on middle, Nortje defends it to short leg this time.
Full ball outside off, it keeps low too. De Kock looks to drive it only to get beaten as the ball sneaks between the bat and pad.
Short ball outside off, de Kock pulls it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Back of a length and outside off, de Kock hops and looks to keep it out only to get an inside edge. The ball goes over the stumps and rolls towards the keeper.
Once again a short ball on off, de Kock pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! The nightwatchman is sent packing and that also is STUMPS ON DAY 2! Coming to the ball, it was  a full ball angled into the off stump, Nortje tries to push it straight to the bowler. In the process he gets an outside edge which flies low towards gully where Joe Denly takes a superb catch.
Wood starts with a full delivery on middle, Philander defends this solidly to the bowler.
Woakes starts with a fuller one outside off, de Kock shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length ball on off, de Kock guides it to gully and takes a single. First run of the day.
FOUR! Punched away nicely! Short ball outside off, Philander stands tall and punches it through the cover region to get his first boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Not the best ball that Woakes bowled but it has fetched him a wicket. Fullish delivery on the pads. Philander looks to flick but it takes the leading edge and goes way up in the air towards cover. Stuart Broad settles himself under it and takes the simplest catches. South Africa still 107 runs behind to avoid the follow-on.
On a length on off, Pretorius looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge and past the diving point fielder. Pretorius is off the mark with a couple.
Full delivery on middle, Pretorius defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish delivery outside off, de Kock shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball outside off, Quinton makes another leave to the keeper.
De Kock shoulders arms to this good length ball outside off.
Fullish outside off, de Kock lets the ball through to the keeper.
Good length delivery on the pads, de Kock looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The ball lobs off to square leg.
Length delivery outside off, de Kock leaves it alone. Maiden over from Wood.
FOUR! Nicely played! Full delivery outside off, Pretorius lunges and drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Dwaine lets it through to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Pretorius defends it to cover.

Woakes dishes a good length ball on middle, Pretorius looks to defend but the ball takes the inside half of the bat and it goes to backward square leg. The batters take a single. 100 up for the hosts.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Back of a length delivery on the pads, Pretorius tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball outside off, de Kock shoulders arms to this one.
Very full delivery on middle, Quinton pushes it back to Wood.
Full delivery outside off, de Kock drives it through the cover region and takes three before Sam Curran can chase it and clean it up.
Back of a length ball on middle, Pretorius defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! This is excellent batting from Pretorius. Wood bowls a full delivery on off, Pretorius lunges and then drives it through mid off for a boundary.

Just short! Very lucky for Quinton de Kock. Broad starts with a full delivery on middle, de Kock looks to defend but gets squared up. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to first slip where the fielder collects it on one bounce.
On middle, de Kock works it to mid on.
Full delivery on off, pushed to cover.
On a length on off, de Kock stands tall and then defends it to cover for a single.
FOUR! That's a top shot from Dwaine Pretorius! Back of a length ball outside off, Pretorius creams the drive through the cover region for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone by Dwaine.
Fullish delivery on off, de Kock pushes it to deep cover and picks up a couple.
Good length delivery on middle, de Kock defends it to mid-wicket.
Full on middle, Quinton prods forward and defends it back to the bowler.
OHH! That was close! Short of a length ball around middle, de Kock looks to defend but it takes the top half of the bat and lobs up in the air. It lands just short of the bowler.
EDGY FOUR! Just wide of Stokes! Fullish delivery around off, de Kock attempts to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes past the diving Stokes at second slip and into the third man fence.
Length delivery on middle, de Kock works it to mid-wicket.

EDGY FOUR! Full delivery outside off, Pretorius looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge and the ball goes past the gully fielder for a boundary. The fielder chases after it but fails to get there in time.
Length ball on off, Pretorius defends it out off the back foot to cover.
Full delivery on off, Pretorius pushes it to mid off.
Full delivery outside off, Pretorius shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Pretorius pushes it to cover.
Edgy! Fullish outside off, Pretorius looks to drive but it takes the inside edge and goes onto hit the pad.
Full delivery on middle, de Kock defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Very well played from de Kock. Short ball around middle, de Kock plays the upper cut over the keeper's head for a boundary.
Short ball outside off, de Kock punches it to deep cover for a single.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle and leg, Pretorius ducks under it.
Length delivery outside off, Pretorius shoulders arms to it.
Full delivery on off, Pretorius defends it to cover.
Very full delivery on off, Quinton looks to dig it out but it takes the inside edge and rolls to square leg. A single taken.
Full ball on off, Pretorius lunges and pushes it to mid off.
Length ball on middle, Dwaine defends it to mid-wicket.
On a length on middle, Dwaine pushes it back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone by Pretorius.
Length delivery on middle, Pretorius defends it towards mid off for a single.
Curran starts with a full delivery on off, Pretorius defends it to cover.
Length ball down the leg side, Pretorius looks to flick but misses.
Good length delivery on middle and leg, Pretorius looks to flick but get hit on the thigh pad. There is a mild appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested.
Full on middle, whipped to mid-wicket.
Full delivery down the leg side, Pretorius attempts the flick but fails to get any bat on it.
Length ball on middle, Pretorius looks to work it to the leg side but gets hit on the pads.
FIFTY! 21st Test fifty! Full delivery on off, de Kock drives it to deep cover for a couple. Only one who has looked good in this innings so far. Can he continue to score a ton here?
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, de Kock pushes it towards mid off.
Length ball on middle, de Kock defends it out.
Length delivery on middle, Quinton defends it towards to mid on.
Fullish delivery on middle, Qdk whips it to mid-wicket for nothing.
EDGY FOUR! Good length ball outside off, Pretorius looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and the ball goes past the gully fielder for a boundary.
On a length on middle, Pretorius works it to mid-wicket.
Curran lands it on a length on middle, Pretorius defends it back to the bowler.
Short of a length ball on middle, Dwaine tucks it to mid-wicket.
Fullish delivery on middle, Pretorius flicks it to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Pretorius looks to drive but fails to get any bat on it.
Back of a length ball on off, de Kock taps it to point.
Short delivery outside off, Quinton pushes it to deep cover for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Pretorius works it to mid on.
Short ball outside off, Pretorius looks to play the pull but fails to get any bat on it.
PLAY AND A MISS! Short of a length delivery outside off, Pretorius goes for the cut but misses to get anything on it.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle and leg, Pretorius ducks under it.
Back of a length delivery outside off, de Kock pushes it to deep cover and takes a single.
Good length ball on middle, Pretorius defends it back to the bowler.
On a length on off, Pretorius stands tall and blocks it to the cover fielder.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Pretorius ducks under it.
Good length delivery on the pads, Pretorius looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad. No harm done.
Comes around the wicket and bowls a length ball outside off, Pretorius shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Quinton pushes it to mid off.
Good length delivery on off, de Kock defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, de Kock pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, guided to gully.
On a length on middle, de Kock pushes it to point.
Fullish on off, de Kock pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball on off, Pretorius defends it to the off side.
Full delivery on off, Pretorius pushes it to mid off.
On off, blocked to cover.
Good length delivery on middle, Pretorius defends it towards mid off.
FOUR! What a shot that is! Full delivery on off, Pretorius prods forward and drives it through extra cover for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, pushed towards mid on.
Short ball on off, de Kock guides it to point.

NOT OUT! It is going over the stumps. Good length delivery around off, swinging into the batsman. De Kock looks to leave the ball but gets hit on the pads. The English players appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Woakes convinces Root to go for the review. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that the ball was going over the stumps. England lose their first review.
Full delivery outside off, de Kock looks to flick but it takes the inside edge and goes towards deep square leg. Two taken.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
On middle, whipped to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball on middle, Pretorius works it to the leg side for a single.
Good length ball down the leg side, Pretorius looks to flick but misses.
Fullish delivery on middle, Dwaine tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Good length ball on off, de Kock blocks it to point.
Fullish delivery on off, de Kock pushes it back to the bowler.
On middle, blocked back to Curran.
FOUR! Lovely batting! Full delivery outside off, de Kock lunges and drives it through the extra cover region for a boundary. 150 up for the hosts.
Full delivery on off, Pretorius pushes it to mid off.
Very full delivery on middle, Pretorius digs it out to mid on.
Full delivery on off, Dwaine blocks it back to Woakes.
Good length ball on off, Pretorius looks to defend but the ball hits the pads. There is a mild appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head.
Outside off, left alone.
Full delivery on off, pushed to mid off.
Short of a length ball outside off, punched to deep point for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Pretorius looks to defend but it takes the inside half of the bat and the ball goes to deep square leg. A single taken.
Good length ball on off, de Kock defends it off the back foot to the bowler.
BEATEN! Nicely bowled! Good length delivery outside off, de Kock looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
BEATEN! Excellent bowling! Length ball outside off, de Kock attempts to defend but misses it altogether.
Good length ball outside off, de Kock shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball on off, defended out solidly by Pretorius.
Full delivery outside off, Pretorius shoulders arms to this one.
On middle, Pretorius tucks it to deep square leg for a single.

FOUR! Beautiful shot from de Kock. Fullish delivery on off, de Kock drives it through extra covers. Wood chases after it and then dives forward but the ball wins the race and enters the fence for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Quinton defends it to the bowler.
Outside off, defended off the back foot.
Back of a length ball on off, Pretorius defends it off the back foot to gully.
Short ball outside off, Pretorius sways away from it.

BEATEN! Nicely bowled! Good length ball outside off, Pretorius looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it. Stokes appeals but the umpire shows no interest. Stokes wants Root to go for the review. Root asks Buttler whether there was an edge but Buttler says no.
Driven towards the mid off region.
FOUR! Driven nicely. Full delivery on middle, Pretorius drives it straight past the bowler for a boundary.
On off, pushed towards mid off.
Full delivery on off, de Kock defends it to mid off.
On off, Quinton blocks it solidly towards the mid off fielder.
Length ball on off, de Kock defends it to point.
Full delivery outside off, de Kock drives it to cover.
Short ball outside off, de Kock punches it to deep cover for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Pretorius defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Cut away nicely! Short ball outside off, de Kock cuts it through the point region for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, defended towards gully.

EDGY FOUR! Back of a length ball on middle, de Kock looks to flick but it takes the leading edge and the ball goes towards deep point. The fielder from deep cover tries to cut it off but fails to cut it off. A boundary signaled.
Full delivery on middle, de Kock works it to deep square leg for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Brilliant from Stokes and Crawley. Finally the stand is broken! Good length ball on off, bounces a little extra then expected. Pretorius looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards gully. Zak Crawley dives forward and takes an excellent catch. How long will they take to wrap up the innings?
The batsman plays it with an angled bat and guides it to third man.
Good length ball on off, de Kock defends it out.
Short ball on middle, de Kock pulls it with disdain towards deep mid-wicket. The fielder comes across and cleans it up. Only a single.
Full delivery on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Short of a length on middle, Hendricks works it to the leg side.
Full delivery on the pads, de Kock looks to flick but misses. Gets hit on the pads.

OUT! BOWLED! What a delivery from Wood to get his fourth wicket. Brilliant stuff from de Kock. Full delivery on off, tailing in sharply. De Kock looks to drive but misses it altogether. The ball goes onto hit the top of middle stump. End of an excellent innings from de Kock. South Africa still 26 behind to avoid the follow-on.
WIDE! Short ball outside off, Hendricks looks to pull but misses. Wide signaled.
Full delivery on middle, Hendricks defends it back to the bowler.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On middle, punched back to the bowler.
Good length delivery outside off, Hendricks pushes it to cover.
EDGY FOUR! Full delivery on middle, Hendricks looks to flick but it takes the leading edge and the ball goes towards the point region for a boundary.
Short ball on off, pushed to the off side.
Good length ball on off, Paterson defends it to cover.
EDGY FOUR! Valuable runs! Full delivery outside off, Paterson looks to swing it away but it takes the outside edge and goes over the slip cordon for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! 5-fer for Wood! Brilliant performance from Mark Wood and he thoroughly deserves it. Full delivery outside off, Paterson looks to drive it off the front foot but it takes the outside edge and goes towards the keeper. Buttler takes the catch. SOUTH AFRICA HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 183.
Philander starts with a length ball on middle, with no swing whatsoever. Crawley stands tall and defends it out.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Crawley pushes it to mid on.
Length ball outside off, Crawley makes a good leave to this one.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley does not fiddle with it and leaves the ball alone.
Length ball outside off, Crawley makes another leave.
Nortje dishes a full ball outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley makes a leave to this one.
Good length delivery on middle, Sibley defends this ball back to the bowler.
England are underway! Full delivery on off, Sibley defends it to cover and takes a single.
Back of a length ball on off, Crawley tucks it to the leg side and crosses over for a single.
EDGY FOUR! Nicely bowled from Nortje. Full delivery on off, Sibley looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes through gully for a boundary.
Full delivery on off, Crawley pushes it to cover and takes a single.
Full delivery outside off, Sibley leaves the ball alone.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
Paterson starts with a good length delivery outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one as well.
Fullish delivery outside off, Sibley allows it through.
Good length delivery swinging into the batsman. Sibley decides to leave it but gets hit on the pads. There is a mild appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head.
Full delivery on middle, Crawley pushes it to mid on.
Short ball outside off, Crawley sways away from it.
Good length ball on off, Crawley guides it to gully.
Length ball on the pads, Crawley looks to work it to the leg side. He misses and gets hit on the pads.
FOUR! Hammered! Short ball on middle, Crawley stands tall and pulls it to the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley works it to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Very good delivery from Patterson. Fullish delivery outside off, Sibley is late in getting his bat down and the ball sneaks under his bat and into the mitts of the keeper.
Good length delivery on off, bouncing a little more. Sibley defends it with soft hands to square leg.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
On middle, Crawley solidly defends it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, tucked to mid on.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley defends it out.
On the bounce! Full delivery outside off, Sibley attempts to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes to second gully on the bounce.
Length ball on middle, Sibley looks to flick but it goes off the pads towards square leg. A leg bye taken.
Full delivery outside off, Crawley defends it out.
Length delivery outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Crawley pushes it to mid on.
Full delivery outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
Fullish delivery outside off, Sibley leaves the ball alone.
Outside off, left alone by Sibley.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley works it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery outside off, left alone.
Length ball on middle, Sibley blocks it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, Crawley works it to mid-wicket.
Short ball outside off, Crawley sways away from it.
Good length ball on middle, with extra bounce on it. Crawley looks to defend but it goes off the gloves towards square leg. A single taken.
Full delivery on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball on off, Sibley taps it to gully.
FOUR! Full delivery outside off, Sibley prods forward and slashes it through the gully region for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Crawley drives it towards mid on for nothing.
On middle, Zak whips it to mid-wicket.
Length ball on middle, Crawley defends it towards mid on.
Full delivery on off, driven to cover off the front foot.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley defends it back to the bowler.
PLAY AND A MISS! Short delivery outside off, Crawley looks to cut but fails to get any bat on it.

Hendricks starts with a length ball on off, Sibley pushes it to cover and sets off for a single. The fielder from point runs ahead and then has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Had he hit, it might have been close.
Full delivery on middle, Crawley defends it to mid off.
Length ball on middle and leg, Crawley flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Thrashed! Full delivery outside off, Sibley takes a stride forward and then drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone by Sibley.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley guides it towards gully where the fielders from point and gully converge but the ball goes in between them. The batters take a couple.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Short ball around middle, Sibley ducks under it.
Full delivery outside off, Sibley makes a leave to this one.
Outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Sibley ducks under it. One for the over signals the onfield umpire.
Good length delivery outside off, Sibley lets the ball through to the keeper.
BEATEN! Lovely delivery! Good length ball on off, tailing in, Crawley looks to defend but the ball goes in between the pad and bat.
Ohh! Good length ball, with extra bounce on it. Crawley looks to defend but it takes the top half of the bat and lobs off towards cover. It lands safely.
Fullish delivery on middle, Crawley works it to the leg side for a single.
Full delivery on off, driven to mid off.
Back of a length ball on off, Sibley defends it off the back foot.
On middle and leg, Sibley works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Crawley blocks it out.
Paterson dishes one on off, Zak defends it to the leg side and shouts a loud no to his partner.

Well fielded! Short of a length ball on middle, Crawley pulls it to deep mid-wicket. Keegan Petersen, the substitute, comes across from deep mid-wicket, dives and makes an excellent save. Keeps the batsmen down to two.
On a length on off, Crawley defends it out.
FOUR LEG BYES! Good length ball down the leg side, Crawley looks to flick but it goes off the pads towards fine leg for a boundary.
Short ball outside off, pulled to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Play and a miss! Shorter in length outside off, Crawley looks to cut but misses the ball altogether.
Full delivery on off, Crawley pushes it to mid off.
Length ball on the pads, Crawley tucks it to deep square leg for another run.
Back of a length ball on middle, Sibley hops and blocks it out onto the pitch.
Short ball down the leg side, Sibley lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Sibley blocks it towards mid on.
Good length ball on off, Crawley defends it to point.
Full delivery outside off, Crawley lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Crawley drives it to mid on and takes a single. Nortje has a shy at the bowler's end and hits but Crawley has made his way in the crease before that.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley lets it through to the keeper.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery! Good length delivery outside off, Sibley looks to defend but it goes in between the bat and pad before travelling into the mitts of the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley works it to mid on and takes off for a single. The fielder comes ahead but fails to collect it cleanly.
Ouch that must have bruised him. Hendricks hits the deck hard on middle. The ball shoots up off the surface. Sibley looks to defend but the ball hits him on his glove and goes to the on side.
Length delivery on off, Sibley defends it off the back foot.
Bowls it in the channel of off stump, Sibley defends it with a straight bat.
On the pads, Sibley looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a stifled appeal for an lbw from the bowler but the umpire is unmoved.

Good ball from Hendricks. It just about pitches on leg and it straightens a bit. Sibley looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on the thigh pad off his back foot. Ohhzz and ahhzz from the South African players but nothing more.
Length ball on off, DS looks to defend but it goes towards point off the outer half of his bat.
Full and shaping away just a tad. Crawley looks to push it straight but it goes off the outer half through covers for a single.
Full outside off, Sibley looks to defend but once again it goes off the outer half of the bat.
Around off, Sibley blocks it.
No swing on this one. It is outside off and Sibley does not disturb that.
Pretorius pulls his length back and bowls it closer to the off stump. Dominic gets right behind the line of it and defends it.

UPPISH BUT FOUR! Just wide of the diving fielder at gully. Good length delivery outside off, Sibley looks to guide it past the man at gully but he does so uppishly. The fielder there dives but it goes just wide of his fingers and to the fence.
Length delivery outside off, Crawley leaves it alone.
Good length ball on  off, Crawley gets on his back foot and pulls it in front of square on the leg side for a single.
Length ball on middle, Sibley looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards mid-wicket.
On off, Sibley defends it with soft hands towards point and takes a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Would have been close had he hit.

In the air but safe. Back of a length on off, Crawley looks to pull but it comes off the upper half of his bat. Luckily for Zak it falls short of Petersen (sub) at deep mid-wicket. A little more of contact on that one and it would have gone straight to him.
On the pads, Sibley looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.

Huge appeal but nothing from the umpire. Good length delivery pitching outside off and coming back in. Crawley looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal but the umpire is unmoved and they take a run as the ball goes towards cover-point. It has been awarded as a run so the ball has kissed the bat.
Outside off, Dominic shoulders arms to it.
Fuller on middle, DS pushes it to mid on.
On a length on off, Sibley blocks it.

EDGED AND FOUR! Full and wide outside off, Sibley stretches and looks to drive but the ball goes off the outer half of his bat and flies through backward point. Pieter Malan tries to stop it with a dive after coming in from deep point but he fails to do so. Brings up the 50-run stand between the pair. These two ended the century run opening stand drought for England in the first innings and are well on course to achieve that once again.
Now calmly leaves this one alone outside off.
Full delivery on middle, Crawley works it to mid-wicket.
Short ball on middle, Crawley pulls it and it goes on one bounce to the mid-wicket fielder.
Outside off, punched off the back foot to point.
Fuller one on middle and leg, Crawley flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short ball around middle, Sibley ducks under it.
Good length delivery on off, Sibley blocks it to cover.
Full delivery on middle, Crawley works it to mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, Crawley defends it out to cover.
FOUR! Creamed! Full delivery outside off, Crawley drives it through the cover region for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pretorius finds the edge finally and Crawley has to go. This is brilliant bowling. Dwaine bowls a length ball around off, moving away with some extra zip. Crawley looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes to the right of the keeper. De Kock makes no mistake. Crawley is visibly disappointed on his way back to the pavilion. Once again he has wasted a start. England lead by 273!
Full delivery outside off, Denly leaves the ball alone.
Fullish on middle, worked to mid-wicket. Successful over comes to an end from Pretorius.
EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball on off, Sibley attempts to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge past the gully fielder for a boundary.
Length ball on middle, Sibley defends it to mid on.
Length ball on middle, Sibley tucks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! This one is timed nicely though! Full delivery outside off, Sibley lunges and drives it through the extra cover region for a boundary.
On off, tapped to gully.
Full delivery on off, Sibley pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Denly defends it out.
Fullish delivery on off, Denly drives it to mid off where the fielder dives and makes a stop.
Length ball on middle, Denly solidly defends it out.

An appeal for LBW shut down. Full delivery on the pads, Denly looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Pretorius and the rest put up an appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Pretorius asks the skipper for the review but Faf thinks that it is going down the leg side. The Ball Tracker confirms that it was going over and away from the stumps.
Outside off, left alone.
Full delivery on middle, Denly defends it out.
Length delivery around off, Sibley shuffles and turns it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Nicely tucked away from Denly. He is a good timer of the ball and gets off the mark in style. On middle and leg, Denly tucks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Now sensibly leaves this ball outside off alone.
Fuller on off, Joe blocks it.

Very good shot but a half stop from Elgar. Full outside off, Denly gets on his front foot and drives it off the middle of the bat in a textbook fashion. Elgar at short cover dives to his left and gets his hands to it. He slows down the ball and Beuran Hendricks tries to pull it back before the ropes and does so successfully. Three taken by the batters.
Full on off, Sibley pushes it to covers and keeps the strike.
On off, Sibley plays it to point and gets to the other end.
A tempter this from Pretorius. It is full and at a nice pace to drive outside off. Denly does not fall in this honey trap and leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Joe pushes it to cover for one.
Length delivery outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley shuffles and looks to defend but gets an inside edge low onto his bat.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

OUT! Played on! The change in bowling has done the trick for the Proteas and Denly joins Zak Crawley in the pavilion. Paterson bowls it full just around off. It nips in a bit. Denly looks to defend but leaves a good amount of gap between the bat and pad. The ball takes the inside edge, hits his pad and then goes onto uproot the off pole. Big wicket for South Africa as Denly has been one of the best batters in this English lineup.
Fuller on off, Root looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge.
Ohh! That was a beauty from Paterson. Full outside off, Root looks to defend but the ball moves away from him squaring him all ends up.
This time Root defends it right off the meat of the bat.
Back of a length on off, JR blocks it off his back foot.
Full on off, Root blocks it to get through the over. Very good first over of his new spell from  Paterson. It's a wicket maiden.
Full on off, Sibley defends it off his front foot.
Away from the off pole and Sibley leaves it alone.
Back of a length on off, Sibley defends it with soft hands towards the off side and gets a single.

FOUR! Tickled away fine down the leg side. It is a full ball on the pads, Root looks to flick but it goes off the inner half and kisses the pads. The ball goes fine down the leg side and goes to the fence.
On off, Root blocks it.
Outside off, left alone by the English skipper.
Full delivery on off, Sibley defends it to cover.
Full delivery on middle, Sibley works it to mid-wicket.
Short ball outside off, Sibley sways from it.

NOT OUT! Beats the inside edge comfortably and it has gone off the thigh pad. Clear day light! South Africa lose their one review. Good length ball on off, nipping back in a shade. Sibley looks to defend after getting across the stumps but it seems to have gone off the thigh pad. De Kock and Paterson are convinced that he has edged that one. They ask du Plessis to go for the review and he obliges. The replays roll in and they show that there is daylight between the ball and the bat. It had brushed the thigh pad and then went into the keeper's gloves.
Full delivery, defended towards cover.
Short ball outside off, Sibley punches it to cover.
Angles in a fuller length ball on middle, Root is right behind the line and offers a straight bat in defense.
Pitches it up and around off, Root is tempted into a drive and does so slightly uppishly. Not carrying to short cover though.
Full delivery outside off, Root leaves it alone.
Full delivery on middle, Root whips it towards mid on.
Full delivery outside off, Root looks to defend but it takes the inside half of the bat and goes towards mid-wicket.
Root solidly defends this length ball on off to cover.
Good length delivery on off, Sibley defends it to the mid on region.
Full delivery on middle, Sibley pushes it to mid on.
Good length delivery outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length ball on middle, Sibley solidly blocks it to short leg.
BEATEN! That's really well bowled by Paterson. Good length ball outside off, Sibley attempts to defend but fails to get any bat on it. Paterson appeals but nothing from the umpire.
On a length on off, Sibley looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Malan starts with a full delivery on off, pushed to point.
Short delivery outside off, Root cuts it to deep point for a single.
Very full delivery on middle, Sibley digs it out back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, left alone by Dominic.
Length ball outside off, Sibley does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
Full delivery on middle, Root drives it straight to the bowler.
Fullish ball on middle, Root whips it to mid-wicket where the fielder makes a half stop and the ball rolls to mid on.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Root looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and goes into the mitts of the keeper.
Down the leg side, Root looks to flick but fails to get any bat on it.
OVERTHROWS! Full delivery on middle, Root works it to mid-wicket. The fielder throws it at the keeper's end and hits the stumps. The ball rolls to deep cover allowing the batters to take a single.
Good length ball on off, Sibley defends it back to the bowler.
Very full delivery on middle, Root defends it out.
Good length ball on middle, Root solidly blocks it out.
That kept very low! Length ball outside off, keeping very low. Root looks to cut but misses it altogether.
Fullish on off, Root defends it to cover off the front foot.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short of a length ball outside off, Root plays the late cut which goes through the gully region for a boundary.
Full delivery on off, Root drives it to covers for nothing. TEA ON DAY 3.
Hendricks starts with a full delivery on middle, Sibley pushes it to mid off.
Length ball on off, Sibley defends it solidly to cover.
Fullish delivery on middle, Dominic blocks it out onto the pitch.
Full delivery on middle, Sibley works it to square leg for a single.
Fullish ball outside off, Root goes for an expansive drive but fails to get any bat on it.
Good shot for nothing! Full delivery outside off, Root drives to the cover fielder.
Good length delivery outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
Another one outside off, Sibley has no intention to play that.
On the fourth stump line, Sibley lets it carry to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley defends it out to cover.
Fullish delivery on middle, Sibley drives it through the mid off region. Keegan Petersen (SUB) races after it and makes a good stop. Three taken.
Short of a length delivery on off, Root taps it to gully.
Full delivery on off, driven to covers for a single.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Root punches it to deep cover for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Sibley goes after getting another start. This is not a wicket-taking delivery but Hendricks won't mind. Beuran dishes a short of a length ball on middle and leg. Sibley tucks it to mid-wicket off the back foot. It goes uppishly, Pieter Malan stationed at mid-wicket tumbles and takes a good low catch. England lead by 309.
Length ball on middle, Stokes defends it out to the bowler.
EDGY! Full delivery on middle, Stokes looks to flick but gets a leading edge which goes towards deep point. A single taken.
Full delivery outside off, Root leaves it alone. End of a successful over!
Full delivery on middle, Stokes takes a few steps forward and blocks it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on off, Stokes comes down the track and then pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! Whipped away nicely. Full delivery outside off, Stokes whips it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Bang! Good length ball on off, Stokes puts on his dancing shoes and hammers it over mid on for a boundary.
Full delivery outside off, Stokes bends to sweep but fails to get any bat on it.
Seam movement and low bounce on this one. It is on a length outside off, Root looks to defend but the ball keeps low and beats him up.

EDGED AND FOUR! Almost chopped on. Good length delivery on off and middle, Root looks to cut but the ball comes in and takes the inside edge of Root's willow. The ball misses the stumps and goes to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Back of a length on off, Root pulls it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Fuller on off, Stokes pushes it to mid off.
Length delivery around off, Stokes dabs it to point.
On a length outside off, Stokes punches it towards cover and keeps the strike.

FOUR! Malan's effort to stop the ball before the fence goes in vain. On middle and off, Stokes flicks it through mid-wicket. Malan gives it a chase and slides and pulls it before the ropes but the ball turns and eventually touches the ropes.
Length ball on off, Stokes taps it to backward point.
Length delivery on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Stokes punches it to cover.
FOUR! Powerful wrist, great eye and great ambition from Stokes. Full outside off, Stokes uses his wrists and whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller on off, Stokes punches it to cover to get through the over.
Good length ball on middle, Root defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish ball outside off, Root pushes it to mid off and takes a single.
Short ball on off, Stokes thumps it over mid on. The ball lands and then stops. The fielder comes across and cleans it up. Two taken.
FOUR! Superb timing. Full delivery on off, Stokes punches it through mid off for a boundary.
Excellent response from the the bowler. Short ball outside off, Stokes does well to sway away from it.

Short ball around middle, Stokes looks to pull but fails to get any bat on it. The keeper is interested for the caught behind but no one else is interested. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there was no bat on it.
Good length ball on off, Root defends it to point.
FOUR! Poor bowling and it has been put away. Low full toss on middle, Root whips it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fullish delivery on off, pushed to mid off.
Length ball on off, Root taps it to point and crosses over for a single.

FOUR BYES! Quinton de Kock was in all sorts of trouble there. Full delivery on off, Stokes jumps across the stumps and looks to scoop it but misses. It hits Quinton who's blinded and turns to evade the bat of Stokes. The ball races behind for a boundary.
FOUR! Cut away nicely! Short ball outside off, Stokes cuts it through the point region for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Root pushes it back to the bowler.
Outside off, Root guides it towards point. The gully fielder comes across, dives but fails to make the stop. The batters take a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Stokes goes after playing a good cameo. He was looking good but now he departs. Good length ball outside off, Stokes goes for the drive without moving his feet. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to first slip. Rassie van der Dussen takes the catch with utmost ease. England leading by 353 runs.
Good length ball on off, Pope defends it to cover.
On middle, Ollie tucks it to mid-wicket.
Short ball on middle, Pope gets off the mark by pulling this to deep square leg for a single.
Fullish ball outside off, Pope shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Pope lunges forward and defends it to cover.
Full on off, Pope drives it but finds the cover fielder.
Good length ball on the pads, Pope tucks it to deep square leg and crosses over for a run.
Full delivery outside off, Root pushes it to cover.
Fullish on middle, Root blocks it to mid on.
Full delivery on middle, Pope works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Nortje dishes another full ball on off, Root pushes it to mid off.
Back of a length ball on middle, Root works it to square leg for another single.
FOUR! Nicely played! Full delivery on middle and leg, Pope drives it through the mid on region for a boundary.
Full on middle, Pope plays it back to the bowler.
Just short! Back of a length ball outside off, Pope looks to cut but it takes the outside edge and goes on one bounce to the first slip fielder.
Fullish delivery on off, Root defends it to cover.
Low full toss on middle, Root flicks it to fine leg and picks up a couple before the fielder can come across and clean it up.
Length ball on off, Root charges down the track and defends it to cover.
Length ball on off, Root guides it to gully.
Fullish delivery outside off, Root lets it go to the keeper.
On middle, Root defends it solidly to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Full delivery on middle, Pope flicks it towards the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nortje gets Pope the second time in this game. South Africa keep on chipping away at the wickets. Short ball outside off, Pope looks to cut but it is too close to him. It takes the outside edge and goes towards the keeper. De Kock makes no mistake and pouches it safely. He celebrates and so do the others. 200 Test dismissals for de Kock. England lead by 367 runs!

Good length ball on off, tailing into the batsman. Buttler looks to defend but it seems to have gone off the thigh pad. The ball lobs up in the air and goes towards gully. Faf du Plessis dives ahead and takes the catch. Nortje appeals for LBW but the umpire is not interested. Faf appeals for the catch as well but umpire shakes his head. The replays roll in and they show that the ball had hit the thigh pad.
Full delivery, driven to mid off.
Full delivery on middle, Buttler works it to mid-wicket for a couple.
FOUR! Absolutely superb! Short delivery outside off, Buttler stands tall and drives it through the extra cover region for a boundary.
Fuller on off, Root defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery outside off, Root dabs it towards backward point and comes out for a single but Buttler sends him back.
Good length delivery outside off, Root punches it to deep point for a single.
Back of a length ball on off, punched to cover off the back foot.
Full delivery outside off, Buttler leaves the ball alone.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to this one.
OUCH! That's nasty! Good length ball outside off, Root looks to defend but it hits the inside edge and hits him around the box. Root screams in extreme pain and crouches to the ground.
Good length ball outside off, keeping a little low. Root looks to defend but it takes the bottom edge of the bat and goes to first slip.
Full delivery on middle, Root works it to deep square leg for a single.
On middle, Buttler works it to deep square leg and takes a couple.
Good length delivery on off, Buttler looks to drive but it takes the inside edge and rolls to the off side.

OUT! CAUGHT! Make that 201 dismissals for Quinton de Kock in Tests. Another failure for Jos Buttler. Short ball outside off, Buttler, without moving his feet, looks to punch but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the keeper. Quinton de Kock won't miss those as he takes a safe catch. England losing wickets in a heap but a lead of 377 runs at this stage has kept them on top!
Good length ball on the middle stump line, Root looks to flick but it hits the inside edge and goes onto the pads. The ball rolls to square leg and they steal a single.
Good length ball on middle, Sam defends it out.
Full delivery on off, Curran defends it to cover.
Short ball around middle, Curran ducks under it.
Length ball outside off, Curran pushes it to deep point for a single.
Good length ball outside off, jagging back in. Root looks to guide but it goes off the gloves towards point for a single
Full delivery on off, pushed to mid off.
Length delivery outside off, Root drives it to deep cover for a single.
Short ball on middle, Curran pulls but finds the mid on fielder.
FOUR! Hammered! Back of a length ball outside off, Curran smashes it through the extra cover region for a boundary.
EDGY FOUR! Full delivery outside off, Curran looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and goes over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Curran taps it to point.
Fullish delivery on off, Root looks to drive but it takes the inside edge and goes onto hit the back knee.
Full delivery on middle, Root moves to the off side, Root works it to deep square leg for a single.
BEATEN! Length ball outside off, Curran prods forward to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
On a length on off, Curran taps it to point and crosses over for a single.
Root defends this length ball on off to point for a single.
Good length ball down the leg side, Curran flicks it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Pulled away nicely. Short ball on off, Curran stands back to fetch it from out there and nails his pull over wide mid on for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Sam pushes it to point for nothing.
Very full delivery on middle, Curran drives it straight back to the bowler.
EDGY! Fullish delivery on off, Curran looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards backward point. Keegan Petersen (sub) comes across and cleans it up. Two taken.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short delivery outside off, Curran punches it off the back foot towards the extra cover region for a boundary. Magical!
Good length ball on off, defended towards point.
Short ball on middle, Root pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Full on middle, Curran taps it to point for a single.
Good length delivery outside off, Root dances down the track and looks to heave it away but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length delivery on the pads, Root flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length ball on off, punched to deep cover for a single.
Full delivery outside off, Root looks to drive but it goes off the inside half of the bat back to the bowler.
FOUR! Hammered! Short ball on middle, Curran pulls it over mid on for a boundary.
Play and a miss! Good length ball outside off, Curran looks to guide it down to third man. Gets beaten.
Full delivery on middle, Curran whips it towards mid-wicket for a couple.
Full delivery on middle, Curran flicks it firmly to deep mid-wicket for a single.
PLAY AND A MISS! Full delivery outside off, Root goes to play the reverse scoop but fails to get any bat on it. Interesting shot selection by the English skipper!
Good length ball outside off, Root guides it to third man for a single.
On the pads, Root flicks it in front of square on the leg side and gets a single.
Length delivery just outside off, Sam looks to cut but misses and gets beaten by a whisker.
This time Curran manages to punch it through the off side and gets a single to bring up the 200 for England.
Just above the stumps. Good length delivery just over the stumps. Root looks to pull but misses.
The batsman works it down the leg side. One run added to the total.
FOUR! Super shot this from Curran. Length ball around off, Sam comes down the track a bit and whacks it through mid off for a boundary.
Good length delivery on the pads, Root looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards the slip cordon and the batters manage to take a leg bye.
Length ball down the leg side, Curran looks to flick but fails to get any bat on it.
Outside off, pushed to point.

OUT! CAUGHT! Short ball does the trick and Curran makes his way back to the pavilion after playing a valuable knock. Hendricks bowls a short ball around middle, Curran looks to play the hook shot but does not time it well. It goes straight into the hands of Dane Paterson at fine leg. England lead by 423 runs.
Good length ball on middle, Woakes looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.

OUT! CAUGHT! Hendricks picks up his fourth wicket and England lose their 8th wicket. Short of a length ball outside off, Woakes looks to push at it tamely and it goes towards the keeper off the inner half of his blade. Quinton de Kock makes no mistake and adds one more to his tally of Test dismissals.
Good length ball on off, Root defends it to cover.
On a length on middle, Root defends it to the leg side.
Fullish delivery on off, Root taps it to point and takes a single.
Good length ball on the pads, Wood looks to work it to the leg side. It hits him on the pads and the ball rolls to point. A leg bye taken.
Fuller one on off, Root moves to the off side and then flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Root guides it to third man for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Joe taps it to the third man region for a single.
Full delivery on off, Wood gets off the mark by driving this to deep cover for a single.

Fullish delivery on the pads, Root looks to play the reverse scoop but fails to get any bat on it. It hits the pads and the ball rolls to the leg side. Hendricks appeals but the umpire is not interested. The batters steal a leg bye.

IN THE AIR... SAFE! Short ball outside off, Wood stands tall to cut but it takes the top half of the bat and goes over towards third man. Faf du Plessis (from the slip cordon) and Temba Bavuma (from 1st slip) run after it but the ball lands safely. Two taken.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Length ball on middle, Wood defends it back to the bowler.
Inside edge! Full delivery on middle, Root looks to flick but it goes off the inside edge towards point. A single taken. An appeal is made for LBW but the umpire shakes his head.
WIDE! Full delivery outside off, Wood leaves it alone. Wide signaled.
Full on off, Wood drives it uppishly towards long off for a single.
Short delivery outside off, Root looks to cut but it takes the inside edge and goes towards fine leg. Faf chases after it and makes a good stop. Three taken.
FOUR! Nicely played! Good length delivery outside off, Wood guides it through gully for a boundary.
EDGED AND FOUR! Short of a length outside off, Wood looks to cut but it goes off the outside edge and over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, pushed to deep cover for a single. 15 runs from the over.
FOUR! Clubbed! Full delivery on middle, Wood heaves it towards the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Short ball on middle, Wood pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Root works it to mid-wicket.
Length delivery outside off, Root puts on his dancing shoes and then looks to heave it away, misses completely.
FOUR! Beautiful stroke! Full delivery outside off, Root drives it to deep cover for a boundary.

FIFTY! 48th Test fifty! The English skipper has made it back-to-back fifties in this Test. He might not be able to convert this into a ton but with this fifty he has given his side a massive lead. This has not been an easy pitch to bat on but he has fought it out in the middle and found a way past his struggles. Length ball on off, Root dabs it towards backward point to his milestone.
Very full delivery on middle, Root works it to deep square leg for a single.

OUT! TIMBER! Another wicket down. Will South Africa get to bat again today? Length ball on off, Wood moves to the off side and then looks to flick. He misses and the ball brushes his pad before going on to uproot the off stump. England are leading by 457 runs.
Good length ball on the pads, Broad works it to square leg for a single.
PLAY AND A MISS! Full delivery outside off, Root looks to heave it away to the leg side but misses.
SIX! What a shot! The sound of the bat meeting the ball was sweet. Full delivery on middle, Root swings it over the deep mid-wicket region for a maximum.
Fullish ball on middle, Root works it to the leg side for a single.
Hendricks comes around the wicket and bowls a short ball outside off, Root punches it to deep cover. Does not take the single.
Outside off, Root punches it to deep point. No run taken.

OUT! CAUGHT! Faf du Plessis takes a stunner to end the innings, the day and also gives Beuran Hendricks a 5-wicket haul on debut. Full ball around off, Root looks to whack it on the off side but gets a thick outside edge which flies to the right of gully. South African skipper, Faf du Plessis decides to show his flying skills and channel his inner Superman. He dives to his right, actually if you see it in real time, you will see him fly like Superman just without the cape and take a blinder with his right hand. People can talk about his age and poor run of form with the bat but boy this man fields like a 20-year old. Root's very good knock needed something special to come to an end and it has taken a spectacular effort to end it. ENGLAND ALL OUT FOR 248! With a lead of 465!
Broad starts the day with a full length ball attacking the stumps, Malan does well to defend this ball out.
Back of a length ball on middle and off, left alone by Pieter Malan.
Another full ball attacking the off pole, Malan shuffles across and defends this towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Fuller one on off by Broad, Malan pushes this one towards the man at cover.
Good length ball attacking the middle pole, Malan defends this one towards the man at mid on.

Ohh! Good delivery to end the over! Length ball on off, angling in, Malan offers no stroke but the ball comes in too much and is hit near the box. End of a good over as England look to attack the Proteas straightaway.
Length ball on off to start with by Curran, Elgar defends it off the back foot towards the man at point.
Curran goes fuller, he defends this one towards the man at mid off.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Elgar.
Good length ball on middle and off, Elgar defends this one onto the pitch and the ball goes above Curran and the man from mid off runs to his left to gather the ball.
Length ball outside off, Elgar defends this one towards the off side.
Outside off, left alone by Elgar.
Length ball outside off to start the over by Malan, he leaves this one alone.
Fuller ball on the off pole line, Malan looks to defend but the ball goes off the outer half towards the man at point all along the ground.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
First runs of the day! On the pads of Malan, he flicks this one towards square leg and gets a couple.
Length delivery outside off, left alone by Malan again.
Good length delivery outside off, Malan leaves it alone to finish the over.

Jaffa! What a delivery by Curran! A length delivery just outside off, angling in. It pitches and then goes away as Elgar looks to play at it. He is completely squared up but the ball beats his outside edge.
Good length ball on middle and leg, pushed towards the man at mid on.
Defended off the back foot towards the man at cover-point.

EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball down the leg side, Elgar looks to work it towards that side but the ball goes off the leading edge behind the man at point and into the fence for a boundary. First boundary of the innings.
Length ball on middle and leg, Elgar looks to defend but is hit on the thigh pad.
Good length delivery on middle and off, defended towards the off side by Elgar.

Huge appeal for LBW but probably going down the leg side. Full on middle and leg, it goes with the angle. Malan looks to flick but misses. There is a huge appeal from the English players but the umpire turns it down.
Good length delivery outside off, asking Malan to have a crack but he calmly leaves it alone.
Broad goes full and closer to the off pole. Malan defends it with surety.
Full on off, Malan pushes it to mid on.

FOUR! Beautiful drive from Malan. Slightly overpitched on off and middle, Malan gets in a good position on his front foot and drives it with class through mid off for a boundary. This will give him a lot of confidence.
Follows the boundary with a calm push to mid off.
Good length delivery outside off, Elgar lets it carry to the keeper.
Full on middle, Elgar strokes it to mid on.

Almost chopped on. Length ball just outside off. Elgar looks to cut but the ball is too close to the stumps and his body. He still goes for it, he ends up chopping it behind and luckily for him and his team the ball does not go onto hit the stumps.
Full on off, Elgar pushes it to mid off.
Full and swinging away from off, Elgar looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and rolls to third a for a single.
On the stumps, Malan defends it with a dead bat.

Stuart Broad produces something special as soon as he comes around the wicket. Good length delivery just outside off, angling in. It pitches and nips away. Elgar looks to play at it but is completely beaten.
Another good length ball on the off side, this time Elgar defends it towards the off side with soft hands and takes a single.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.

Appeal turned down! Good length ball just outside off, coming in. Malan looks to defend this off the front foot but misses to get hit on the back leg's thigh pad. The England players appeal but nothing from the umpire. The impact looks outside off and Ball Tracker confirms it.
Length ball on off, defended towards the off side and Malan rotates strike.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on off, Malan plays a beautiful shot through the cover-point region and the batters take a couple.
On the pads of Malan, he flicks this one towards the mid-wicket region and the batters take a single.
FOUR! Well played but a bad ball! On the pads of Elgar, he flicks this one in the gap near square leg and the ball races away to the fence.
Once again on the pads, played towards square leg again but this time just a run.
Fullish delivery around off, pushed to the man at mid off.
Another one on off and fuller in length, defended towards the man at mid off.
Good running! Wood starts with a full ball on off, Elgar plays it with soft hands towards the off side and takes a very quick single. Intent!
Good length ball on middle and leg, defended towards the man at short leg.
Full ball on middle and off, defended back towards Wood.
Length ball on off, played towards the man at point.
Bouncer down the leg side, Malan ducks and lets it go.
Full ball on middle and off, Malan pushes it down the ground past the man at mid on and the batters take a couple to end the over.
On the pads, flicked towards the man at square leg.
Another one on the pads, played towards the man at mid-wicket.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Back of a length ball on the off side, defended towards the man at point for a single.

Outside off, Elgar leaves this one alone and gets through the over. South Africa have scored 25 runs at the end of the the first 10 overs of the day, but more importantly, they have not lost a single wicket so far.
Length ball outside off, Elgar leaves this one alone.
Another one outside off, left alone.
Another length ball which is outside off, Elgar does not fiddle with it.

Another appeal turned down! Length ball down the leg side, Elgar looks to flick this one fine but fails to do so. The ball deflects off his thigh pad towards Pope at short leg. He takes the catch and the England players appeal but the umpire turns it down. Replays confirm it did not hit the bat nor the glove.
Length ball on middle and off, defended.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Good length ball outside off, Malan looks to bend and defend but he misses the ball and is hit on the thigh pad.
Length ball outside off, left alone.

This time a louder appeal by England but again turned down! Good length ball just outside off, Malan looks to defend but fails to do so. The ball lobs towards the man at silly point who takes the catch and appeals. The umpire again shakes his head as he reckons this one has come off the pads of Malan. England opt against taking the review. Ball Tracker comes in and shows it was hitting the pad and the impact was outside off.
Outside off, Malan does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Another back of a length ball on off, Malan rocks back and cuts and it goes just above the man at gully and into the third man fence.
FOUR! Just pure timing on this one! Good length delivery around off, Elgar hangs on his back foot and uses the pace of Wood and just taps it through point for a boundary.
Length delivery on off stump this time, Elgar defends this towards mid off.
Bouncer! A very well-directed one by Wood. Elgar ducks under it awkwardly but no harm done.
Another short ball. This one is outside off and Dean sways away from it in a better way.
After going short on the previous two balls, Wood goes very full on off. Elgar defends it to the left of the bowler. Wood goes to ground and gets his hand to it and deflects the ball to mid on.
Absolute peach to end the over. Wood hits the deck hard outside off, it looks to be coming in with the angle but straightens up as it comes off the pitch. Elgar looks to defend but gets squared up.
Fuller on off, Malan blocks it.
On a length on off, Pieter defends this.
Woakes goes full on off, PM once again uses a dead bat to see it off.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Length ball on off, Malan pushes it wide of cover for one.
On the hips of Malan, he tucks it on the bounce to short leg.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Malan once again plays it well as he glances it onto the ground towards short leg.
Outside off, Malan lunges forward and lets it carry to the keeper.

FOUR! Classic cover drive. You can keep on watching this shot on loop and you will continue to admire this every single time. Full around off, Malan gets on his front foot and leans into the cover drive. The outfield is quick so the fielder has no chance stopping that.
Short ball, Malan ducks under it.
Good length ball on off, Malan pushes it wide of cover for a run. He will keep the strike.

OUT! CAUGHT! Malan departs and maybe it is a commentator's curse after all. Just as we said the openers cannot lose their concentration, Malan loses his focus, maybe the break in play brought about his downfall. Woakes is the man who has drawn first blood here. Full and wide outside off, Malan goes chasing after it like a kid chasing candy. He ends up getting a thick outside edge which goes to the right of Ben Stokes. You cannot keep him out of the game and he takes a good catch. Catching practice at slip for Big Ben. The steady opening stand has been taken down.
Good length ball on off, van der Dussen blocks it.
Outside off, left alone.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

NOT OUT! Rassie survives. Good referral by the South African no. 3! He lives to fight another day. Good length ball pitching around off, van der Dussen looks to defend but misses. The ball hits him high on the pads of his back leg. The English players go up in a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Rassie has a word with his partner and then signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and first Ultra Edge confirms that there is no bat involved. Ball Tracker then rolls in and it shows that the ball is pitching in line, the impact though is Umpire's call. Then time to see whether the ball is hitting the stumps or not. It shows that the ball was going over the stumps.

Another huge appeal but this time the umpire shakes his head. Very full on off and it nips back in. Rassie looks to play but gets a feather on it onto the pads. The English players are once again excited but this time the umpire is not.
Good length ball on middle and off, defended back towards the bowler.
Length ball on middle and off, Elgar defends it towards the man at mid off.
Outside off, Dean leaves this one alone.
Full ball on the off pole line, defended back towards the bowler.
Woah! Jaffa by Curran! Bowls a back of a length delivery just outside off, and this time gets it to nip back in. Elgar looks to defend but the ball cuts him in half and oohs and aahs all around.
Wide! Bouncer on middle and leg, Elgar ducks as it is way too high.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Good length ball on off, Rassie blocks it off the back foot and into the ground.
FOUR! Short ball on middle and Rassie takes the full toll of it. He just pulls it with disdain and the ball races to the mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Oh! The inside edge there. Rassie looks to defend this length ball off the back foot only to get an inside edge onto his pads.
BEATEN! Beauty of a nut there. Rassie is lured into poking this length ball outside off. Luckily he does not edge it behind.
Outside off, pushed to the man at cover.
Outside off, driven towards point for a couple.
Length ball outside off, Elgar defends the ball off the outside half of the bat towards covers.

Oh! That beats Elgar. He would have had his heart in his mouth. He looks to poke this length ball outside off but the ball sneaks past the outside edge and the ball lands into the mitts of the keeper.
Elgar blocks this length ball off the back foot and towards the covers.

FOUR! Elgar has played that superbly. Dean pushes this length ball outside off straight down the ground and the ball beats the dive of the mid off fielder running to his left and it rolls towards the long off fence for a boundary. 50 comes up with this for South Africa.
Elgar keeps out this length ball outside off.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball outside off, pushed to covers off the front foot.
Rassie pushes the ball off the back foot towards the bowler.
Back of a length ball on off, Rassie looks to pull but is beaten to get rapped on the thigh pads.
Length ball outside off, pushed back to the bowler off the back foot.
Van der Dussen once again pushes this length delivery on off towards the bowler.
Rassie does well to keep this length ball out off the back foot.
BEATEN ! Curran makes the ball curve away from the forward push of Elgar. Dean is lucky there to not edge it.
Elgar pushes this length ball straight towards covers.
On the pads of Elgar. He just flicks it through fine leg and gets an easy single there.
Van der Dussen just taps this length ball off the front foot towards covers.
Back of a length ball on off, kept out off the back foot towards cover.

FOUR! Curran errs in line and dishes one onto the pads of van der Dussen. He just flicks it off the back foot and the ball rolls over the mid-wicket fence. The fielder in the deep cannot do anything there.
Length ball outside off, further going away. Elgar lets it be.
Length ball on off, defended off the back foot.
Elgar blocks one off the back foot there.
Dean defends this length delivery off the front foot and onto the ground.
Elgar drives this full ball outside off towards point.
Last ball of the over. Elgar keeps it out.
Full on middle, Rassie flicks it straight to the man at mid-wicket.
Full and angled away outside off, Rassie looks to lay bat on ball but he misses it.
Angling away outside off, Rassie lets it go through to the keeper.
Once again, outside off, van der Dussen leaves it for the keeper.
Length and around off, Rassie blocks it off the front foot.
Full ball on off, defended off the back foot there by van der Dussen.
Back of a length ball on middle, Elgar blocks it back to the bowler.
Short ball on off, Dean ducks under it.
Length ball on off, played off the front foot there by Elgar.
Length ball on off, Elgar pushes the ball off the back foot towards point.
Outside off, pushed to covers for a single.
Full ball on off, Rassie drives it towards mid off and keeps the strike.
Tossed up on off, pushed towards covers.

FOUR! Beautifully played there by van der Dussen. Root bowls a full ball on middle, Rassie sees the length and promptly gets in position to reverse sweep it. He gets the placement right and the ball races to the third man fence for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up on middle, tucked to short leg.

FOUR! Tossed up on off, van der Dussen dances down the track and flicks this one. He hits it just over the leaping short mid-wicket fielder there and the ball has enough in it to roll over the boundary cushions at mid-wicket.

FOUR! Three boundaries in the over for van der Dussen. Rassie is getting a move on here. Introduction of spin has helped the batter there as he once again reverse sweeps it to find the fence at third man.
Full ball on middle and leg, defended towards the bowler.
On the pads, flicked towards deep square leg for a single by Elgar.
Good length delivery on middle and off, defended.
Fullish ball on off, pushed to the man at mid off.
FOUR! Driven away! Full ball on off, van der Dussen comes forward and drives this ball through the cover region for a boundary.
On the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR BYES! The trap was set there. Root tossed one up on middle and leg, van der Dussen tries to tuck it but the ball just about bounce a tad and it evades the keeper and the leg slip fielder on its way towards fine leg. The umpire gives it as byes.
Root bowls one on the pads and Rassie tucks it to leg slip.
Tossed up on off, kept out.
FOUR! Now van der Dussen plays the conventional sweep and finds the fence. Full and on middle this time, Rassie sweeps it through fine leg and the ball meets the fence in no time.

SIX! Van der Dussen is taking Root on. 50-run stand up between van der Dussen and Elgar. Rassie skips down the track and hoicks one over the fence at mid-wicket. The fielder there is a mere spectator as the ball sails way over him and into the stands.
Full on the pads, tucked to mid-wicket.
Length ball around off, defended back towards the bowler by Elgar.
Outside off, left alone by Dean.
Bouncer on middle and off, Elgar ducks under it.
Good length ball just outside off, defended by Elgar back towards the bowler.

OUT! Caught! The budding stand has been broken and it is Ben Stokes who is once again in the thick of action. A very good ball this from the English all-rounder. He bends his back and bowls a very good short ball. The speed gun shows it is bowled at 136 kph but in real-time it looked quick. It is very close to Elgar's body and the ball skids off the surface. Elgar is hurried onto the pull and all he can do it lob it back to Stokes who takes an easy catch. Just when it looks like South Africa are onto something England put a brakes on it and dampen all the hopes. The pitch is hardly doing anything but Stokes once again shows why he is held in high regards and produces something special.
Hits the deck hard on the stumps, Faf du Plessis starts his innings with a back foot defense.
Tossed up on off, defended back to the bowler.
Full on leg stump, tucked past short leg and the batsmen take a run.
Full on middle, Faf defends it right under his eyes.
Tossed up on middle, Faf tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Full ball on middle, du Plessis does well to turn it towards mid-wicket.
Floated on middle, du Plessis does well to block it back to the bowler. That will be LUNCH ON DAY 4!
First ball of the post Lunch session and Stokes bowls it on a length outside off. It comes back in but Rassie is aware of his off stump and lets it be.
Calm and composed start from van der Dussen as he once again does not go after a length ball away from his stumps.
Stokes goes full and close to off stump, van der Dussen squeezes it to deep point for a single.
Oh! Stokes hits the deck hard around off, it swings away just a hint. Faf looks to defend but gets beaten.
Closer to the off stump, du Plessis blocks it with a straight bat.
Good length delivery on off, Faf lunges forward and defends it towards cover and calls his partner to wait.
Full and on off, Rassie drives if off the inside half of the bat towards mid on.
BEATEN! Beautiful delivery! Van der Dussen is squared up there as he looks to push this length ball outside off from the back foot.
Back of a length ball on middle, Rassie hops and defends it towards mid-wicket.
Full ball on off, van der Dussen drives it back to the bowler.
Fuller and outside off, Rassie drives it straight to covers.
On a length and on  off, Rassie taps it to covers off the back foot.
Back of a length and on off, Faf looks to flick it to the leg side. But extra bounce there means that the ball raps the gloves and rolls towards the off side.
Length ball outside off, Faf lifts his bat and lets the ball through.
Back of a length ball on off, Faf taps it towards short leg .
Length ball on off, du Plessis looks to defend it but the ball takes the inside edge and hits Faf on the box.
EDGED BUT SAFE! Length ball outside off, Faf looks to go for the drive through covers. But the ball takes the outside edge and rolls towards second slip.
Outside off, kept out off the front foot.
Length ball on off, Rassie drives it towards covers.

FOUR! Too full from Wood and van der Dussen pounces on it as he drives it past the bowler all along the ground showing the full face of the bat. No need to move there as the ball hurries to the long off fence.
Length ball outside off, Rassie shoulders arms to it.
Short ball on middle and leg, van der Dussen ducks under it.
Full and on off, Rasssie drives it towards mid on.
Short and on middle, van der Dussen pulls it all along the ground towards mid-wicket for a run.
Short of length ball outside off, van der Dussen hops and defends the ball off the back foot towards covers.
Effort ball from Stokes there. It is angled right on the body. Rassie looks to pull it only to miss it. The ball sails past the ears of van der Dussen and into the mitts of the keeper.
Full on the pads, van  der Dussen flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a run.
