NOT OUT! Faf survives. Bad review from Root there. Stokes bowls a length ball outside off, Faf looks to leave it but gets something on it on the way to the keeper. Buttler there takes the catch and immediately goes up in appeal. The umpire shakes his head. Root straightaway signals the 'T' because he definitely heard something there. The replays roll in to show that yes, it did hit something but it was not the bat or the glove, and instead it was the elbow. Faf continues to fight it out in the middle for himself and the team.
Bumper once again, Faf is quick to spot it and sways away from the line of the delivery.
Full and on middle, flicked straight to the man at mid-wicket.
On the pads, played towards mid-wicket.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Rassie.

Full ball on the pads, van der Dussen flicks it towards deep mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep runs to his left and cuts it off but the batters in the meantime take three quick runs. 100 up for South Africa with this too.
On the pads again, flicked towards mid-wicket for a single.

50 for Rassie van der Dussen! His 3rd Test half ton and he will be delighted with this one. A good length delivery bowled near the off pole line, Rassie pushes it towards mid off and takes a single to get to this milestone. However, he knows that his work is not even half done and he needs to convert this  into a big one if his side is to win this game.
Du Plessis shoulders arms to let this one through.
The short ball barrage continues as van der Dussen drops his wrists and sways away from the line.
Another bouncer and Rassie goes for the pull only to miss it as the ball sails over him. Buttler looked excited but aborted the appeal as the umpire was not interested.
Third one in a row and Rassie ducks under it. The umpire penalizes Stokes by giving it as wide.
Back of a length on off, van der Dussen hops and defends the ball towards point.
Full toss outside off, Rassie punches the ball through covers and gets to the other end.
Length ball on off, Faf pushes the ball towards mid on off the back foot.
Full ball on off, Faf looks to defend it but the ball goes past the short leg towards deep square leg. The batsmen get a couple.
Stuart starts his new spell with a length ball outside off, Rassie leaves it alone.
Length and outside off, van der Dussen taps it towards point and calls for a quick single. The batsmen get it easily.
Length ball on off, pushed back to the bowler off the back foot.
Faf defends this length ball on off towards mid-wicket, who fumbles and the ball goes towards mid on.
Full ball on off, du Plessis pushes it back to the bowler.
Length and outside off, Faf punches it towards covers off the back foot.
Length and outside off, Rassie guides it to gully.
Full on the pads, Rassie flicks it through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Outside off, Faf is happy leaving it.
Du Plessis looks to tuck this length ball on middle and leg towards mid-wicket but he misses to take the blow on the thigh pad.
Length and on off, Faf pushes the ball towards covers.
Back of a length ball on middle, Faf hops and flicks it toward short mid-wicket where the fielder fumbles and the ball rolls towards mid-wicket which allows Faf to retain the strike.
Good length ball on middle and off, defended back towards the bowler.
Length ball just outside off, left alone comfortably by the skipper.
Length ball on middle and leg, worked towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Flicked away! On the pads, du Plessis plays a wristy shot towards the mid-wicket region and the ball races away to the fence.

Woah! What happened there? Broad bowls a length ball just outside the off pole line, the skipper chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump. The ball pitched and kept very low. Had that come in enough, it would have meant trouble for Faf. Replays roll in and show that it had come off the crack and that is why it stayed so low. England will keep looking for those now!
Back of a length ball on off, defended off the back foot.
FOUR! Supreme drive! Full ball on off, van der Dussen comes forward and he drives this one through the cover region for a boundary.

Woah! What a bouncer that one and it has been theatrically left alone by van der Dussen too! A short ball, 141 kph, van der Dussen first thinks about playing at it but leaves it alone in the end and falls down in the process.
Good length delivery on middle and off, defended back towards the bowler.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side for a single.
Another bouncer, this time Faf does well to evade it.

Ouch! Nasty, nasty delivery! Du Plessis has taken off his glove and is looking in some pain. Back of a length ball on middle, Faf looks to defend it off the back foot but he is hit on the glove. Looks like this has impacted his thumb more than anything else. The physio has come out to aid the South African skipper.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by van der Dussen.
Another good length ball, this time on middle, worked towards the square leg region for a single.

Down the leg side, du Plessis looks to flick this one towards the leg side but he misses his flick and the ball goes off his pads towards the left of the keeper who dives and the batters steal a leg bye.
Rassie van der Dussen has now been hit on the glove. Not too bad though as he continues.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Good length ball on middle and off, van der Dussen looks to defend but the ball goes off the inside edge and onto the pads.
Bouncer on middle, a fierce one, du Plessis does well to sway away from it.
Full ball on off, pushed towards cover for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full ball on middle and off, driven towards the man at mid on.
Another one which stays low after hitting the crack! Short delivery around off, the ball pitches and stays low to hit Rassie van der Dussen on the hips as he hops and looks to defend.
Good length ball just outside off, Rassie looks to work it towards the leg side but the ball goes off the outside edge towards gully for a single.
Good length ball on off, played towards point for a single.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Length and on off, Faf looks to push this ball but he gets an inside edge onto the boots and the ball rolls towards point.
Length and outside off, Faf presents the full face off the bat as he blocks it off the front foot.
Good length on off, pushed to mid on off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, Faf pushes it to covers.
Back of a length ball on off, Rassie hops and defends it to the leg side.
Full on off, Rassie drives this towards covers and shouts a loud no.
Full on off, driven towards mid on.
Full and outside off, brilliantly driven but superbly fielded at covers by Dominic Sibley.
Full on the pads, van der Dussen flicks it straight to the man at mid-wicket.
Length and on off, pushed back to the bowler off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, pushed towards cover-point for a single.
Full ball on middle and off, van der Dussen drives this one towards cover but Sibley there makes a superb diving stop.

Length ball outside off, van der Dussen looks to defend but fails to do so. It hits something and lobs towards the slip cordon where the fielder comes forward, takes the catch and appeals. The umpire shakes his head. Replays roll in to show that this had hit the thigh pad.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Van der Dussen has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the pads works this one towards the leg side.
Length ball on middle and off, defended off the back foot onto the pitch.
Good length ball on middle and off, du Plessis looks to defend but gets an inside edge on it. The ball rolls just past the off pole and misses by a whisker.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball on middle and off, du Plessis looks to defend but misses.
On the pads, du Plessis has worked it off his pads behind square. One run added to the total.
Back of a length ball on middle, van der Dussen defends it off the back foot.
Length and angling into the batsman. Faf defends it back to the bowler.
Full and on the pads, Faf flicks it to get an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batsmen cross ends.
Length and on off, driven towards covers.
FOUR! Beautifully played that! Full and outside off, Rassie van der Dussen drives it off the front foot. The ball goes behind square on the off side and rolls to the fence  there.
Full on the pads, Rassie flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length and on off, Rassie leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle and off, defended towards the man at mid off.
On the pads, flicked towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Better this time! Down the leg side again, van der Dussen just tickles it fine down the leg side for a boundary.
Length ball on middle and off, du Plessis looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. The England players put in an appeal but it is waived away by the umpire.
Another one on the pads, again Faf looks to flick but misses.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full ball on off, pushed towards cover for a single.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.

EDGED AND FOUR! Length ball on off, du Plessis looks to drive but the ball goes off the outside edge through the slip cordon and the gully fielder for a boundary. 50-run stand comes up with this boundary.
Length ball on middle and off, defended back towards the bowler.
FOUR! This time much better by du Plessis! Back of a length ball on middle, du Plessis rocks back and pulls this one through square leg for a boundary.
Length ball on middle and leg, du Plessis plays it back to the bowler.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Pushed to the cover region by the batsman. They pick up a single.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Good length ball on middle and off, pushed back towards the cover region.
Length ball just around off, du Plessis defends it onto the pitch.
Full ball on off, played straight to the man at cover.
Full on the off stump, Rassie pushes it towards covers and gets to the other end.
Tossed up on off, driven towards covers.
Faf drives this full ball towards long on for a single.
Faf now drives this full ball towards mid on for a single.
SIX! Tossed up on off, van der Dussen dances down the wicket and lofts this over the cow corner fence for a biggie.
FOUR! Brilliantly done. Van der Dussen dances down once again and drives this towards long on for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Faf tucks it to mid-wicket for a run.
Length ball on off, pushed towards covers.
Length ball on off, Rassie looks to lay bat on ball but it sneaks past the outside edge.
Short ball on middle, Rassie ducks under it.
Full and on the off stump, Rassie defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Full on the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Floated on off, pushed towards cover for a single.
FOUR! A freebie by Denly and it has been hit away! Full toss on middle, van der Dussen dances down the track and he has smashed that down to the long on fence for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, pushed towards cover.
Floated on off, defended towards cover.
Van der Dussen pushes this one towards the mid on region and takes a single.
The batsman dances down the track but decides to defend it. Good over for the Proteas again.
Back of a length ball on off, Rassie hops and defends it from the crease.
Full and on off, Rassie drives it towards covers for a single.
Well-directed short ball, Faf sits under it.
Length ball on off, Faf looks to defend it off the back foot. The ball bounces a bit extra and pings du Plessis on the glove. He loses his grip on the bat too as he throws it away.
Another bumper in the over but down the leg side. Faf does not fiddle with it.
Length and on the pads, Faf tucks it to square leg and takes a run.
Full on off, pushed to covers.
Tossed up on off, Faf drives it to find mid off to perfection.
Floated ball on off, Faf tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Run off a misfield! Faf drives this full ball straight towards mid off where the fielder slides and parries it towards long on. The batsmen take a run.
Outside off, defended to the off side.
Tossed up on off, pushed to covers.
FOUR! Du Plessis sees the length early and flicks it off his pads. The ball rolls all along the ground towards mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full and on off, Faf defends it by going low.
Faf flicks it off the back foot towards mid-wicket.
Faf is happy to defend it towards covers off the back foot.
Length ball outside off,Faf punches it off the back foot towards covers where Broad dives to his left and fields it.
Outside off, kept out off the back foot.
FOUR! Length ball outside off, van der Dussen cuts it off the back foot through cover-point and the ball runs to the fence at deep point.
Length and outside off, left alone.
Full and on  the pads, Rassie flicks it towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
Good length and outside off, Faf is in no mood to touch it.
Back of a length ball on off, Faf blocks it off the back foot.
Back of a length ball on middle, Faf hops inside the crease and defends it towards mid on.
Short ball but wayward. Rassie ducks it.

EDGED AND FOUR! That was an educational edge there. Rassie van der Dussen moves into the nervous 90s. He looks to keep out this length ball outside off but the ball just about manages to take the outside edge and fall short off the diving gully fielder. The ball goes past him and into the fence at third man.
Length and on off, pushed to cover off the back foot.
Length and on off, pushed to the off side off the back foot.

Ouch! That might have sent shivers down the spine of Rassie van der Dussen. Wood goes short and directed on the body. Rassie looks to leave it by dropping hos wrists but the ball does not bounce as expected and it hits his chest hard. Rassie is onto his knees as he waits for the physio to attend to him.
Another ill-directed bouncer, Rassie lets it go.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Faf du Plessis departs after a fighting knock but for England, Ben Stokes is the man yet again! Stokes bowls a length ball just around off, it pitches and nips back in a bit. It also hits the crack and that makes the ball stay low. Faf du Plessis looks to come forward and defend but the ball goes off the bottom edge, onto the turf and then onto the middle pole to dislodge the bails. The skipper departs and a huge, huge blow for the Proteas!
Back of a length ball on off, Quinton de Kock punches this ball off the back foot towards cover for a single. Gets off the mark!

Another one which was almost chopped on! This is Ben Stokes at his best! Bouncer just outside off, van der Dussen looks to hop and defend. The ball goes off the inside edge onto the turf again but this time past the stumps. Van der Dussen survives and England smelling blood here.
FOUR! Good comeback by Rassie van der Dussen! Full ball on the middle and leg pole line, van der Dussen drives this one straight back down the ground through mid on for a boundary.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side for a single.
Good length ball on middle and off, defended back towards the bowler.
Back of a length ball on middle, Rassie plays it to mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! The nervous 90s bug has bitten Rassie van der Dussen as he takes a long walk back to the dressing room. He looks dejected. Rassie was expecting some chin music there with the field spread out. However, Wood surprises him with a full ball on off. Seeing the length, van der Dussen's eyes lit up and he goes for the expansive cover drive. He does not time it perfectly and it goes a touch uppishly to the right of Stuart Broad who tumbles low in that direction to take a good catch. Wood deserves this wicket more than anyone as he has been bowling well all day. Van der Dussen misses his ton by two runs and England get two wickets in two overs.
Outside off, left alone.

Lucky man! Bavuma is lucky not to lob this to the close in fielder. Bouncer on middle and leg, he looks to flicks it off the back foot but the ball goes off the glove and lobs wide of short leg and short of backward square leg. The fielder there looks interested a bit but the ball drops in front of him.
Length and outside off, left alone by Bavuma.
Outside off, pushed towards covers.
Length and outside off, de Kock lets it be.
Short ball on off, Quinton lets it go through.
Back of a length ball on middle and leg, de Kock tucks it towards fine leg and rotates the strike.
Full outside off, Bavuma shoulders arms to it.
Length ball outside off, Bavuma plays it with an angled bat towards gully.
Length ball outside off, Bavuma leaves it to see of the session. TEA ON DAY4!
Good length ball on middle and off, to start with by Woakes, de Kock blocks it out.
This time a fuller ball on the middle and leg pole line, played towards the man at mid-wicket.
Good length ball on the off pole line by Woakes, de Kock defends it.
Full ball on the off pole line, de Kock defends it off the front foot onto the ground.

EDGED AND FOUR! Lucky break for Quinton de Kock! A length ball, pitching and angling away from de Kock. He looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge between third slip and gully and the ball races away to the fence.
Length ball on middle and off, defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Length ball on off, Bavuma rocks back and blocks.
Another back of a length ball, Bavuma looks to defend but the ball hits his glove and falls down on the leg side.
Outside off, Bavuma does not fiddle with it.
On the pads of Bavuma, he works this one towards the leg side.
Outside off, Temba does not bother to play at it.
Length ball outside off, Bavuma guides this one towards the man at point.
Back of a length ball outside off, de Kock plays this one towards the point fielder.
Another back of a length ball on off, this time de Kock plays it in the gap at point and takes a single.
FOUR! Creamed! Full ball on off, Bavuma drives this one beautifully through the cover region for a boundary. Gets off the mark with probably the shot of the day!

FOUR! This time an educational edge! Length ball outside off, Bavuma looks to guide this towards third man but it goes finer than he expected and the ball races away to the fence. 200 comes up for South Africa with this.
Outside off, Temba leaves it alone.
Another one outside off, Bavuma does not fiddle with it.
Length ball outside off, Quinton drives this one towards cover-point and gets to the other end.
Length delivery outside off, Bavuma lifts his bat and lets it go.
Bavuma looks to flick this back of a length ball to mid-wicket but the ball goes towards mid on.
Back of a length ball on middle, Bavuma flicks it towards fine leg. The fielder there was much squarer and that allows the batsmen to take a couple.
BEATEN! Back of length ball on off, Bavuma looks to punch it off the back foot the ball bounces a bit more and goes past the outside edge.
FOUR! Back of a length ball on off, Bavuma punches it past point and the ball races to the fence behind.
Good length and on off, pushed to mid off.
Another back of a length ball on off, chopped towards point.
Full and on middle, de Kock drives it with a straight bat towards mid on.
FOUR! Pulled with disdain. Woakes goes short and on middle, de Kock pulls it off the back foot into the gap at mid-wicket to find the fence.

FOUR! Back to back boundaries. De Kock is showing his class here. He is not going to give up there. He comes on the front foot to this pitched up ball and drives it srisply through covers. Not a fielder moved as the ball met the fence.
Back of a length ball outside off, de Kock goes for the cut but edges it in the process. The ball rolls towards the slip cordon.
Back of a length ball on middle, defended by Bavuma.

FOUR! Smashed away! South Africa not hiding anymore! Back of a length ball on middle, Bavuma rocks back and pulls this uppishly towards square leg and the ball crosses the ropes on a couple of bounces.
Length ball on off, pushed towards cover for a single.
On off again, this time de Kock plays it towards point for a single.
Bouncer on middle and leg, Bavuma ducks under it.

EDGED AND FOUR! Bavuma flirting with danger here. Almost a bouncer on off, Bavuma hops and looks to cut. The ball goes off the edge and above the man at third slip and into the third man fence. Matter of inches there and Stokes would be wishing that he was standing there instead of his skipper to add those extra inches.
Full ball on middle, played towards the man at mid on.
On the hips, de Kock looks to flick but is hit on the thigh pad instead.
FOUR! Driven away! Full ball on middle and leg, de Kock has driven this one down the ground through mid on for a boundary.
The batsman defends it from within the crease. One run added to the total.

FOUR! Super shot from Bavuma! Back of a length ball on off, Bavuma has driven cut that one through the point region and the ball has raced away to the fence. Partnership moves to 48 runs with this one off just 51 balls.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Bavuma has to depart and that is a cracking nut by Broad! Broad bowls a bouncer on middle and off, Bavuma hops and first thinks about playing at it but then realises that it is too high. He tries to drop his hands but by then the ball goes off his gloves and into the mitts of Buttler who takes an easy catch. Broad gets his first wicket of the Test match and he has shown his class against the youngster. Half the side back in the hut for South Africa.
Good length ball on the pads, de Kock looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. De Kock crosses for a leg bye as the ball rolls towards the leg side.
This time on the pads of Pretorius, he flicks this one towards mid-wicket and takes a couple. He is off the mark with this.
Length ball outside off, moving away, Pretorius shuffles but lets it be.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Another one outside off, left alone.
Pretorius shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
On the pads, worked towards square leg for a single.
Bouncer on middle and off, Pretorius does well to sway away from that.
Outside off, left alone.

OUT! CAUGHT! Stuart Broad is a tall man and it is very difficult hooking him and Pretorius departs in that very attempt! Bouncer on middle and leg, Pretorius goes back and looks to pull but gets a top edge on that one. It goes towards backward square leg where Sam Curran runs in and takes a very good catch diving forward. England 4 wickets away from the win.
Length ball outside off, de Kock plays an exquisite square cut but it goes straight to the man in the deep and the batters take a single.
Length ball on middle and leg, Philander looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Floated on off, driven towards the man at cover.
Floated on off again, pushed to the man at cover.
Tossed up ball outside off, de Kock tries to go for the slog sweep but misses it as the ball spins away.
Flatter one on off, defended by de Kock.
Again de Kock drives towards the cover region but finds the man there.
Tossed up delivery on off, defended towards the off side.
Length delivery on middle and off, defended.
FOUR! Philander is off the mark in style in his final test innings! Length ball outside off, Philander rocks back and cuts this one through the point region for a boundary.
FOUR! Another back of a length ball on middle, Philander rocks back and now pulls it in front of square leg for a boundary.
Philander goes back in his crease and defends this one out.
Length ball on the hips, Philander looks to pull but the ball goes off the inner half towards the leg side and the batters take a single.
FOUR! Stand and deliver from Quinton de Kock! Full delivery on middle and off, de Kock just smashes this one over mid on for a boundary.
Floated on middle and leg, defended towards the leg side.
Another one on the pads, defended out.
Philander pushes this one down towards the leg side and takes a single.
The batsman opens the face of the bat and helps it to third man.
De Kock has played this one towards the man at mid on.

SIX! A huge one and first one of the innings for Quinton de Kock! Floated delivery on middle and off, de Kock goes down on one knee and this time connects with his slog sweep as he sends this delivery into the stands at the mid-wicket region.
Bouncer on middle and leg, Philander looks to hook but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Philander departs and the whole crowd stands up and applauds the great man. He raises his bat as he accepts the applause and walks down the tunnel being a proud man having given his all for the nation. Back of a length ball down the leg side, Philander looks to tickle it fine down the leg side but he gets a faint edge on that and Buttler does well as he dives low to his left and takes the catch. The England players appeal and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. England 3 wickets away from the victory.
Length ball on middle and off, defended by Nortje.
Length ball on off, Nortje defends it out.

Shouts of catch it but no one there! Length ball on middle, Nortje looks to work this one towards the leg side but the ball goes off the leading edge uppishly towards cover-point but there is no one there and the batters take one.
FOUR! Whatever happens at the other end, de Kock looks unfazed! Length ball outside off, de Kock rocks back and cuts this one through the point region for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Anrich prods forward and defends.
Floated on off, blocked out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Tossed up on off, Nortje plays the reverse sweep and gets a single.

A loud appeal for LBW but it has been turned down. Root bowls a slider on off and middle, de Kock is late in bringing his bat down in time. The ball struck him high om the pads there. The English players appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Maybe, it hit the batsman high.
De Kock drives this through the covers. One run added to the total.

OUT! CAUGHT! Chris Woakes takes the catch and this has to be the final nail in the coffin for South Africa. Back of a length ball on middle and off, Quinton de Kock looks to pull but he only manages to get a top edge on this one. The ball goes up in the air towards mid off where Chris Woakes runs across and takes the catch. De Kock throws his wicket away and England heading to a comfortable victory.
Back of a length ball on middle and leg, defended by Hendricks by getting up on his toes.
On middle and off, pushed towards the man at mid off.
Way wide down the leg side, Hendricks goes after it but misses.
Back of a length ball on middle, Hendricks pulls but straight to the man at square leg.
A short delivery which has been pulled away. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Tossed up on off, defended by Hendricks.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Just about misses the leg pole. Root floats it up on off, Hendricks looks to play at it but the ball goes off the inside edge past the leg pole and towards fine leg and the batters take a couple.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball. The batsmen have run through for a single.
On the pads, worked towards square leg for a couple.

OUT! RUN OUT! Disaster strikes and that is a shambles as Hendricks departs now. Full ball on middle and leg, Nortje plays this one down to mid on and sets off for a run. Hendricks does not have eyes for his partner and is ball-watching. Nortje has reached the non-striker end and Hendricks is at the same end as well. Hendricks runs towards the striker's end but Sibley at mid on collects the ball and has the presence of mind to throw the ball at the striker's end. Buttler collects the ball and whips the bails off with Hendricks well short. England just a wicket away from victory!
Short ball on middle and leg, Nortje ducks under it.

OUT! CAUGHT! ENGLAND HAVE WON THE MATCH! Nortje is the last man to depart. Wood takes the final one. Not the best of the balls but England and Root will take it. Wood bowls one down the leg side. Nortje looks to go for a fine tickle but fails to do so as it goes to Buttler. The England players immediately go up in appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Root immediately signals the 'T' and the replays roll in. Ultra Edge shows that there was a spike as the ball went past Nortje's glove. The umpire reverses his decision and that will be all. ENGLAND SEAL THE SERIES 3-1!
